formatted_address: 25, Jalan SS 15/4b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: JIBRIL SS15

reviews.text:
Spaghetti was good, our kids love it! the ambience were romantic and calm.

Chicken buttermilk were too sweet to my liking. Lobster were delicious. The sauce are pretty spicy.

Overall the food can be made better, the services can be improve.

I had a good experience dining at the viral café. The food was enjoyable, but the pasta was quite spicy and overly creamy. I couldn’t finish it as it became too rich after a while. I also ordered a drink called "Cleopatra," which had a fancy name but turned out to be an F&N soda with starfruit. Overall, the café’s dark-themed ambiance added to the unique experience.

The standout dish at Jibril is definitely their **salted egg croissant**. Even as someone who usually doesn’t like croissants, I loved it! The croissant is flaky on the outside and perfectly soft inside, filled with a rich, creamy salted egg yolk sauce that balances sweetness and saltiness so well. It’s definitely a must-try!

However, their **mango mocktail** was a bit too sweet for my taste, with a slightly off flavor. We also ordered another drink that turned out to be sold out, but we weren’t informed until we asked, which was disappointing. Hopefully, the service improves in that aspect.

The restaurant is hidden and quite dark inside, creating a romantic atmosphere, perfect for a date with your loved one.

As for the other dishes, the **fried sweet potato** was just average, and the **buttermilk chicken** wasn’t what I expected. But if you’re visiting, I highly recommend trying the **salted egg croissant**—it’s the real highlight!

The establishment's ambiance and overall environment were highly satisfactory. The culinary offerings were of exceptional quality and aligned perfectly with my personal preferences. I anticipate revisiting this establishment in the future.

Call me crazy but I think they've actually improved the quality of their food. Butter chicken and fried sweet potato were excellent and we would gladly come back just for them. They also have SaltCola which you should try.

However, the chili butter clams were rather disappointing; it wasn't spicy at all. I hope you put spicyness level in your menu or get your waiters to ask how spicy we want it to be.

Service was excellent. They're short-staffed, but on the flip side, they won't sit you unless they can serve you. Food came out quick, surprisingly

formatted_address: 10, Jalan USJ 11/3j, Usj 11, 47620 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: The Bear Hug

reviews.text:
Surprisingly Good! Their signature fried rice is home cooked flavourful 👍🏻 & it comes with the seafood gravy (reminds me of fatty crab), it blends so well! Will definitely come back again for their signature seafood fried rice. It’s not oily greasy too.

Dessert: Taro Sandwich Green Tea Cake is 💯

Price is 🆗 affordable.

I had the pleasure of dining at Bear Hug Restaurants today and tried a few dishes that truly impressed me. The Carbonara was creamy and flavorful, striking a great balance with just the right amount of richness. The Ra Mien noodle soup was a pleasant surprise with its comforting broth and well-cooked noodles. To top it off, the Red Date desserts were a perfect way to end the meal—sweet but not overly so, with a unique flavor that lingered pleasantly. The ambiance was cozy, and the staff was attentive, making the overall experience enjoyable. I’ll definitely be back to explore more of the menu!

Delicious food, cosy and clean environment, easy parking and welcoming atmosphere located in USJ 11’s neighbourhood. My top favourites are  the seafood sweet and sour with mantou (burst of flavours), grilled chicken chop (not oily and sauce on point), the grand finale is the 5 stars lemon cake (surprisingly light, not sweet with perfect hint of lemon). Husband and wife, run the cafe with lots of passion and love for food ❤️🐻

I ordered the smoked duck carbonara, and the portion was surprisingly generous, even enough to feed a whole crowd! Not only was it large, but the dish was also absolutely delicious. I highly recommend dining here, but can also order takeaway or through Grab as well.

Came here twice and will come back for more. Will not discover this place if not because of Myra, her schoolmate parents run this place, KK and AW

Fried salted chicken thigh Nasi Lemak is a must try. Nasi is really fragrant however it's cold, if only it's hot hot hot, the whole dining area will smell so good! 🤣🤣 Sambal is spicy, just nice for me, donno if ask for more will get charge or not 😋. The fried chicken is yumzzzz, crispy skin and juicy meat! If only the telur mata yoke is still runny, would have been perfect!

Superior soup ramen with grill chicken chop is surprisingly good! We gave it a try as its something different from other restaurants! Soup is sedap..

The portion is generous and friendly price...

formatted_address: G-3, Grand Subang, Jalan SS 13/3, Subang Jaya Industrial Estate, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Dae.Janji Restaurant Subang

reviews.text:
Dae.Janji Restaurant in Subang truly impresses with its creative fusion menu and cozy ambiance. Here’s my take on the dishes I tried:

1. Buttermilk Chicken Pasta
This dish hits all the right notes! The creamy buttermilk sauce is rich yet not overpowering, perfectly complementing the tender, flavorful chicken pieces. A well-balanced and satisfying meal for pasta lovers.

2. Honey Butter Chicken Chop
The chicken chop is crispy and juicy, with a delightful honey-butter glaze that adds a perfect blend of sweetness and savoriness. The portion size is generous, making it a standout option.

3. Sweet Potato Fries
A great side! These fries are crisp on the outside and soft on the inside, with a natural sweetness that pairs wonderfully with the provided dipping sauce.

4. Ice Lemon Tea
Refreshing and tangy, this classic drink is the perfect companion to the rich flavors of the dishes.

5. Strawberry Sago with Coconut Jelly
This dessert steals the show! The fresh strawberry flavor, combined with chewy sago pearls and smooth coconut jelly, is a refreshing and delightful way to end the meal.

Overall, Dae.Janji delivers a fantastic dining experience with its creative menu and warm service. Highly recommended for a casual meal or gathering with friends!

Big portion at reasonable price - if this criteria is what you're looking for, then head to Dae Janji, a cafe taking a prime spot in Grand Subang SS13. Parking can be tricky as most road side spots are taken up as experienced by yours truly during the visit there.

Unmistakably a bright and modern cafe, the service was warm from the moment I stepped in. We were quickly ushered to the first floor as downstairs were packed to the brim.

◾Hainanese Chicken Chop - their take on this classic Hainanese western dish was commendable. Fairly big piece of deep fried chicken smothered in sweet savoury tomato based sauce on top of bed of mashed potato and salad on the side. Loved the
◾Fried rice with fried chicken - lacking the essential wok hei but made up with that ridiculously crispy yet juicy whole chicken leg, and that still-runny fried egg yolk.
◾Curry Noodle - surprise surprise! The curry broth was actually very nice despite not having any expectations - balanced in between curry spices & coconut milk. It'd be perfect if the presentation is better.
◾Wantan soup tasted just like those that I had at my regular wantan noodle shop.

Those who are looking for big portion at affordable price, this is it!
Excellent food and great coffee. Recommend to try the salad. Ordering done from QR code, makes things easier. Friendly service.

4.9/5!

It’s good and pretty interior. Food is good Toilet is clean. And the table& chair are comfortable
Ada 2 floor so boleh buat event.
Food portion is big. So if you’re a not a big eater, share with a friend.

I prefer if there’s more kuah. But it’s fine. The ayam is so crispy and huge. Berbaloi. I makan chicken chop percik.

Loved the desserts here! The strawberry sago was so refreshing, with a nice balance of sweetness, and the matcha taro was creamy and rich. Both were delicious and beautifully presented. Definitely worth a try!

formatted_address: 42, Jalan SS 15/4b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Warong Samad

reviews.text:
I would've rated the food 4 and overall 4.

Overall the food is good and everything is well cooked except the chicken used was too old for both the dishes we ordered.

The key ingredient fell short due to lack of freshness. Other than that, it is not bad in terms of taste and portion.

the last time I visited this restaurant was last year, and I must say, their nasi buttermilk chicken is still very delicious! the chicken is nice and juicyy and the buttermilk sauce goes perfectly with it😋 one thing I like about their sauce is that it doesn't give me that 'muak' feeling after eating it. I also ordered their strawberry tea and it was delicious!!! will definitely visit again and bring my family and friends 🩷

I find the food here very delicious, got homemade feel and price also quite affordable. I try the buttermilk chicken because someone recommend on Twitter, and it suits my taste. You all should come and try, sure won't regret! They got many other menu also, worth to explore.

Plus, very convenient to get here, just a short walk from LRT SS15 station, so no excuse not to drop by!

Food was good, drink was good. The portion is quite alot for me. Hardly find this kind of portion nowadays. The taste also quite good, as i dont really like Buttermilk Chicken, but i enjoyed and finished this one. 5 stars!

I actually like the nasi ayam percik (see photo). The last time I tried meehoon goreng pun sedap.

There is set meal (exclusive set meal) where you order rice + drinks for between RM14-RM18. Environment is cosy and service is friendly. Order and pay at the counter.

Located on the same row with mypizzalab and opposite gigi coffee, finding a parking would be a mess during rush/peak hour.

formatted_address: 6, Jalan 21/11b, Sea Park, 46300 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Bumbung

reviews.text: The place is so easy to find and it’s located in between the shop lots. The shop opens until 12 am but they open till 12:30 am since some customers come late. Just one request for the customers, please go there before 12 am since the workers also need to do their closing and back home. One of the craving nasi lemak in KL and it’s really taste good. They also have Burnt Cheesecake and Mango Stick Rice as an extra menus. Must try nasi Lemak and thank me later.

The place was very crowded at night, and I had to wait in line for a few minutes. I tried the nasi lemak ayam goreng for RM 8, and it was quite tasty. It's a great spot for nighttime dining with an open space.

Nasi lemak with fried egg and fried chicken cost RM8. Nasi has 'lemak' taste.. Chicken was slightly hard and sambal was not one of the best. However, the fried meehoon was good. Was not dry n had tomatoes which gave it both a savoury, spicy from the chili and sweet / sour from the tomatoes. Rendang chicken was alright too.

Dnt know how long ago was my last visit. Came here on a Monday night and didn't need to wait for a table which was nice.

This time round- I didn't wanna have their nasi lemak, I went for the Maggie goreng and it was satisfying. Good flavor. Somehow they cut the noodle into shorter length:') other than that, not bad at all!

The fried chicken is nice especially the outer layer, somehow the meat didn't felt like the spice went in. It was moist though.

I've been a frequent visitor for the past 20 years. I've always liked their food . Started off with indo Mee and today they've got varieties and even started with a POS system to collect payment from customers. I used to admire all their staff's super quick maths during the "boss Kira" time. Their service is really fast and accurate most of the time. In terms of cleanliness you can't expect much because your seating areas are between road alleys. Honestly the drain and cockroaches freaks me out. Other than that this place brings me back to my teenage days. I will only order their indo Mee and Milo Ais and that's the best.

formatted_address: 26, Jalan SS 15/8b, ss15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Burung Hantu

reviews.text: I heard and saw this place in IG and was excited to try but it's nowhere close to the nasi Lemak ayam berempah at oriental Kopi which as fresher, crispier and far larger pc of juicy chicken. Unfortunately I wouldn't come back. Everything pales from rice to egg and chicken. Not good. Average. Doesn't even visually look appealing.

The nasi lemak was okay. The rice is fragrant enough, their sambal is spicy and slightly sweet. However, their ayam goreng was a miss for me. It was dry & not juicy compared to the OG👑. 4pc petai udang costs RM12+ so total RM32 for the whole meal pictured, it’s really overpriced! I think it’s okay to try once and see if it suits your tastebuds but I personally prefer VP 😅 even Nasi Lemak Shop (for the same price) tastes better for me 🥹

One of the best nasi lemak ive tasted, they’re using basmati rice and they gave free kangkung, sambal was also spicy enough and the ayam rempah was just as good as it looked🤤 the sambal udang was good too but a little pricey for 4 pcs of udang.

The waiters were very helpful to find seats for customers and they’re also very patient and polite even during peak hours. 👍 definitely will come back for more

Nasi Lemak Burung Hantu SS15 was bustling with locals, creating a lively atmosphere. A helpful staff member quickly found us a table despite the crowd. The long queue took about 15 minutes to reach the counter. Unfortunately, the food was underwhelming. The sambal kerang was overly sweet and salty, and the nasi lemak, while fragrant, was disappointingly dry. The ayam goreng berempah was average, and the sambal served with the nasi lemak was also too sweet. The highlight of the meal was the kangkung and the refreshing Iced Sirap Bandung. Overall, the experience didn’t match the value, especially compared to my previous visit to their Taman Tun Dr Ismail branch, where the food was much better. Next time, I'll satisfy my nasi lemak cravings elsewhere.

Nothing special with this nasi lemak besides being pricey. Fried chicken is just plain fried chicken. Sambal is too sweet. Rice is basmathi. Kangkung is just plain boiled. Not sure what the hype is, I tried. So not a place worth goin to Q again.
Fried chicken from village park or Ratha Raub is better than here. Sambal from Warisan Opah is better.
You want basmathi nasi lemak bungkus (RM3), go to coconut shop beside Moorthy.
Q here is long and wait is long because you need to wait for them to fry the chicken which finishes fast. Could be faster if they allow those who just want plain nasi lemak without chicken to have their order.
Don't go believe all paid reviews.

formatted_address: 39-1 & 41, 1, Jalan USJ 9/5p, Subang Business Centre, 47620 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Murni Discovery USJ 9

reviews.text: Myself along with family & friends have visited this place a bunch of times more than I could even count. Among the rest of the food I’ve tried, nothing beats their classic Nasi Lemak Biasa, Naan, & Maggie Germany. Portion is reasonable, price is not expensive, and their taste is pretty delicious as well. Ordering anything outside of these options then the price will defer accordingly (can be expensive depending on what you order). But if you don’t intend to overspend or on a tight, their classic and basic is the way to go along with their teh tarik terapung. Their standard hasn’t dropped one bit over the last 10 years and more. Would definitely continue to recommend and bring my family and friends to this place.

Went here as adhoc option to dine-in, as the shop that we wanted to go was closed earlier than its operating hours.

As usual, Murni is always crowded with diners and we were lucky as during our visit (before 7pm), we managed to secure a seat.

Similar like other outlets, the waiters collected orders using their apps. Ordered Mee Raja + was a bit disappointed with my choice. It should be called MAGGIE RAJA, not mee. Thanks to Chicken Chop, our dinner adalah rasa sikit. Likewise, it tasted bland and my son didn't like it.

As for drink, I ordered warm water but the waiter gave cold water. Not a big deal but it was a big disappointment when Murni served me with a RO water bottle. I was expecting for an established shop to serve a mineral water, not RO water.

Not sure will come here again as we all know, Murni's food are quite expensive. The drinks mungkinlah berbaloi to buy.

Stayed here till 8pm as we were waiting for ShopeeFood and we could see so many GrabFood drivers outside the shop, delivering food orders.

Love the vibes here. Always packed and crowded but the air conditioning and fans  keep the place cozy. Dishes are interestingly named 😃❤️⭐️ For example: Nasi Goreng Ecuador, Nasi Goreng Bechkam, Spaghetti Benzema 🤣🤣. Love their soup Dejamoo, various types of nasi goreng are also good, as well as their mee raja 👍⭐️. Overall western food here is so so only, chicken chop not bad. Indomee double is really cheap cheap good good 😂👍⭐️.. this place famous for its food that are reasonably priced. As long as you don’t go for it’s fancy drinks you are set for a hearty and value meal ⭐️❤️👍. Well done Murni! Keep it up! Came here for supper during Euro 24. Small screen but good enough ! Awesome!! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Much better taste compared to previous cooking. Big portion and reasonable price.

My favorite pandan chicken is in this place. Always go any outlets for it whenever come to KL.

Hubby ordered nasi lemak and big signature drink. He likes it too.

formatted_address: G10, Oasis Business Center BU4, Changkat Bandar Utama, Bandar Utama, 47800 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: nasi lemak shop.

reviews.text:
Amazing nasi lemak spot in Bandar Utama! This place is so popular that there’s always a queue, but it’s absolutely worth the wait. The restaurant is modern, clean, and the service is impressively quick. The food? Simply delicious!

The nasi lemak with fried chicken was a standout — the sambal was perfectly balanced, and the crispy chicken skin added an irresistible crunch. The mee siam was another winner, packed with flavor. Don’t miss the kaya toast — rich, creamy, and the perfect sweet treat to round out the meal.

Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great food and a welcoming atmosphere. I’ll definitely be back!

I am not a connoisseur of Nasi Lemak, but this place is a good option to get an interesting experience of this popular dish.
It’s usually crowded during lunch, so you might need to plan ahead.
The service is good and people there are nice.

I went here after this place was the talk of the town. I heard they are serving the best nasi lemak. Unfortunately, the nasi lemak was just below average. Nothing to hype about to be honest. The sambal is honestly tasteless for us and don't have the umphh at all. The fried chicken was moderate like 5/10 rating as I have eaten the best fried chicken at some other places. Portion wise it's normal serving for an adult. Price wise I felt it's a little expensive but okay to try once. The atmosphere was unpleasant where the tables are too close to one another which is quite uncomfortable. You guys could try once as our taste buds are not the same.

Long queue and large crowd during lunch hour but the restaurant did well to accommodate people while queueing with having a large tent with air cooler and seats also providing drinks and snack while waiting. Staff is helpful and friendly.

Restaurant have outdoor seats along the corridor and indoor with a long bar table and tables seat but little bit tight space due to space of restaurant not too big.

We had the Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng, Mee Siam Curry Chicken and lemon barley.
The rice have slight coconut fragrance aroma while the sambal spiciness and sweetness just nice and balance. The highlight would be the ayam goreng with just fried freshly and hot. Chicken meat is tender and juicy with skin is crispy with well marinated rempah. Plenty of crispy fried rempah given on top.
Mee Siam is delicious and curry chicken is flavourful with thick and heavy curry. Portion of curry chicken and potatoes also generous.
Lemon barley surprise us as it is not those sweet with syrup type. Plenty of barley on the bottom with slight lemon aroma in it.

Definitely one of best nasi lemak I had.

The Nasi Lemak berempah is really yummy, fragrant rice and tasty crispy chicken.
White curry noodles is nice, quite lemak and the sambal sotong is a good addition.
Prawn noodles was so so, not that special.
Dry mee siam is tasty as well, quite tasty, with the curry chicken.

formatted_address: 2, Jalan SS 5a/9, Ss 5, 47301 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Restoran Subang Ria

reviews.text: Food was decent. But not the best.. i have tried their famous chili pan mee. It tasted so so. Just over-hyped from the internet.  Came during off peak hour on Sunday around 11.30pm not so crowded. Parking was based on luck. QR pay is accepted but better to prepare some cash to pay drinks to the waitress when it arrives. The surroundings are quite clean and safe.

Came over here out of curiosity. We ordered:

1. Dry Chilli Pan Mee x2
2. Chicken Rice
3. Popiah Basah
4. Fried kuey teow

Dry Chilli Pan Mee: It is as good as it gets. No MSG so that is plus one. But nothing special

Chicken Rice: Stingy on the soy sauce, could have added more. The rice was on point

Popiah Basah: was very meh. The chilli paste was not smeared equally. Tasted very bland. Didnt finish it.

Fried kuey teow: I saw a lot of people ordering it so i ordered it. The wok hey is on point. HOWEVER there is no taste at all. Only taste so salty. Didnt finish it.

Overall: not worth the hype.

We came here with Daniel for breakfast, and we were overwhelmed with the various choices available to us. Each stall at this restaurant offer different type of good, and most of them seemed very appealing to us.

My stomach was not feeling so well since yeaterday, so I only ordered Kaya Toast with half boiled eggs. Both my wife and Daniel decided to have the Special Penang Fried Koey Teow, with extra prawns and cockles. Basically everything was in the superlatives, and they ended up not finishing their meals!!

I guess we will have to come back and try the other stalls...

Nice food, fast serving at affordable price. This is the first time I visited Malay restaurant with Chinese hawker style. Environment a bit hot. My colleague highly recommend the pan mee and indeed taste good. She love to visit here because not easy to get halal pan mee around PJ area. Drink was ok. Easy to get car park here.

Taste of Char Kuey Teow special RM 13 each. Quite pricey. Yong Tau Fu quality still maintained. The Rojak Mamak peanut sauce was too thick. Parking is based on luck. Restaurant closed at 3 pm after lunch crowd.

formatted_address: 43, Jalan SS 23/15, Taman Sea, 47400 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Serunai Nasi Lemak

reviews.text: It’s a very cosy and spacious dining area. Thumbs up to all the staffs here. Very friendly and attentive. Very hardworking as well. Always making sure the place is clean. Fried chicken was really good.  The rice and sambal can be better as mine was a bit cold. Overall not bad

Place is spacious and well ventilated. Service is good.

However nasi lemak is okay. Sambal feels overwhelming and might take some time to like. Curry chicken is not what expected. Kunyit too strong. Fried chicken is okay.

Teh tarik is not good, got the tannin aftertaste.

Cham ais is good.

Tempeh crispy was okay, didn't expect it to taste sweet.

First impressions, very cozy outlet without the need of ac. Outlet ventilation is good and it won't be hot. Nasi lemak is creamy for the rice and the sambal is something special than the rest, with lots of onions in it and I dig it. Ordered Ayam Goreng Berempah, yummy and flavourful yet juicy.
Also had the cendol too. Nice~

2024-Sep
the fried rempah is the only thing i think is acceptable.
the sambal is too salty.
I ordered 4 chickens, but none is thigh. But still its chicken breast is still acceptable.
The nasi itself is not fragrant enough.
The price is still reasonable, but i hope you may improve your food quality.

Finally tried the famous Serunai. It was quite a disappointing experience to be honest. The sambal was really bland and lacked flavour. The rice was too was dry. Fried chicken was nice and the other side dishes were just okay.
