formatted_address: 10, Jalan PJS 6a, Kampung Lindungan, 46000 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Limoka (Petaling Jaya)

reviews.text:
Food is tasty, price is just a little bit on the high side. The lempeng is great, I personally enjoyed it! Friendly and responsive service crews. The sweetness of our drinks is alright (we asked to reduce sugar, which they did & didn’t not ruin the overall taste).
The shop is a little bit small and so be mindful of the crowd.

If you’re on the hunt for a killer nasi lemak, let me tell you, this place is a hidden gem that could easily fight  with another legendary nasi lemak spots near Damansara Uptown. The rice is perfectly fragrant, cocooned in that rich coconut goodness, and the sambal? Oh boy, it packs a punch without setting your taste buds on fire! The crispy anchovies and peanuts add that delightful crunch, while the perfectly boiled egg just ties everything together like a bow on a present. Honestly, I could eat this for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. If you’re a nasi lemak aficionado, do yourself a favor and check this place out. It’s a flavor fiesta that’s definitely worth the trip!

This restaurant had only started operating in January this year, but lately it had been aggressively "viralled" in social media outlets. This had prompted my wife to keep on nudging me to try it out. And finally, this morning we had the opportunity to do so.

It is located only about 3 kilometers from where we live, but the neighborhood was not very familiar to us. Upon our arrival, it was a total surprise to us to find such a modest and unassuming place, but it had a unique rustic charm to it. Being situated directly facing an apartment dwelling would ensure a constant market and demand, as long as they serve good quality foods..

My wife immediately ordered Lempeng Pisang (Flat Banana flapjack), as well as Lempeng Kelapa...as if those were not sufficient, she also requested for Kaya Toast with Half boiled eggs on it, what they referred to as Roti Titab. Not to be outdone, I also decided to indulge myself with a glorious serving of Nasi Lemak, which came with a Fried Chicken Leg masak rempah, Sambal Kerang (cockles), and Paru Goreng. I guess both of us would be skipping lunch, based on the hefty breakfast we had taken.

As expected, my wife didnt or couldnt finish one of the lempengs she had ordered, and had to pack it to go. Together with Teh Tarik and Ice Tea, the total bill came to RM51.00, which my wife insisted was quite steep, but I thought the Nasi Lemak alone was worth the price. It is quite rare for people to serve nasi lemak with add ons, as you could adjust your orders according to your heart's desire. I found that the Sambal Kerang was very tasty and delicious, albeit a bit too spicy for me. And I would always prefer for all the sambals to be separated from the main nasi lemak plate. In this particular serving, they were all jumbled up together, except for the Sambal Paru, which was a tad to spicy also.

My wife was also not very satisfied that her Teh Tarik was served in a cup, instead of a mug or glass. I couldnt agree more with her, but my order of Ice Tea was properly served in a tall plastic glass, so I had nothing to complain about...

Ok been hearing a lot about this shop recently and had to check it out. Ok first thing is parking here is limited so on a crowded day it might be tough to get a spot. The shop isn't that big as well but they have an open air section and an AC section. The staff are super friendly. Now the interesting part is their name. Limoka was named as such as 'li' came from the area Limdungan, 'mo' was contributed from motosikal as the original shop was lindungan motor and lastly 'ka' for kafe. A very neat branding.

Ok the nasi lemak is flavourful. I personally didn't think the rice was heavy on the santan. The taste was there but it was light for me. The sambal was slightly on the spicier side rather than sweet but not overpowering. The ayam goreng berempah was decent. Overall a good plate of nasi lemak but wasn't outstanding. I'm not saying it's bad ya, don't get me wrong. It's good but I don't get the wow factor. Rather than the nasi lemak goreng berempah, I thought the ayam rendang was better. The rendang was damn flavourful. If I return I would opt for that instead. This shop also sells lempeng which is hard to find nowadays. Price wise some ppl might say it's expensive but it's marketed as a kafe so the prices are on par with that. I would say it's worth coming by and trying it for yourself

This place is a hidden gem. Both of us tried the Nasi lemak Ayam Berempah, definitely bomb! One of the best in town, this will be my new go to whenever I’m craving for Nasi lemak. Fried chicken flavourful, tender and juicy! The crisp outside well made, will melt in your mouth. This is also my first time trying lempang Kelapa, great stuff.

formatted_address: G10, Oasis Business Center BU4, Changkat Bandar Utama, Bandar Utama, 47800 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: nasi lemak shop.

reviews.text:
Amazing nasi lemak spot in Bandar Utama! This place is so popular that there’s always a queue, but it’s absolutely worth the wait. The restaurant is modern, clean, and the service is impressively quick. The food? Simply delicious!

The nasi lemak with fried chicken was a standout — the sambal was perfectly balanced, and the crispy chicken skin added an irresistible crunch. The mee siam was another winner, packed with flavor. Don’t miss the kaya toast — rich, creamy, and the perfect sweet treat to round out the meal.

Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great food and a welcoming atmosphere. I’ll definitely be back!

I am not a connoisseur of Nasi Lemak, but this place is a good option to get an interesting experience of this popular dish.
It’s usually crowded during lunch, so you might need to plan ahead.
The service is good and people there are nice.

I went here after this place was the talk of the town. I heard they are serving the best nasi lemak. Unfortunately, the nasi lemak was just below average. Nothing to hype about to be honest. The sambal is honestly tasteless for us and don't have the umphh at all. The fried chicken was moderate like 5/10 rating as I have eaten the best fried chicken at some other places. Portion wise it's normal serving for an adult. Price wise I felt it's a little expensive but okay to try once. The atmosphere was unpleasant where the tables are too close to one another which is quite uncomfortable. You guys could try once as our taste buds are not the same.

Long queue and large crowd during lunch hour but the restaurant did well to accommodate people while queueing with having a large tent with air cooler and seats also providing drinks and snack while waiting. Staff is helpful and friendly.

Restaurant have outdoor seats along the corridor and indoor with a long bar table and tables seat but little bit tight space due to space of restaurant not too big.

We had the Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng, Mee Siam Curry Chicken and lemon barley.
The rice have slight coconut fragrance aroma while the sambal spiciness and sweetness just nice and balance. The highlight would be the ayam goreng with just fried freshly and hot. Chicken meat is tender and juicy with skin is crispy with well marinated rempah. Plenty of crispy fried rempah given on top.
Mee Siam is delicious and curry chicken is flavourful with thick and heavy curry. Portion of curry chicken and potatoes also generous.
Lemon barley surprise us as it is not those sweet with syrup type. Plenty of barley on the bottom with slight lemon aroma in it.

Definitely one of best nasi lemak I had.

The Nasi Lemak berempah is really yummy, fragrant rice and tasty crispy chicken.
White curry noodles is nice, quite lemak and the sambal sotong is a good addition.
Prawn noodles was so so, not that special.
Dry mee siam is tasty as well, quite tasty, with the curry chicken.

formatted_address: 5, Jalan SS 21/37, Damansara Utama, 47400 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Village Park Restaurant

reviews.text:
This place is super popular with locals and tourists, dine in and takeaways also.

Outside the eatery are neatly arranged rows of chairs  fully occupied by food delivery riders waiting for their pick ups.

Needless to say, food is good, service is systematic and efficient.

Highly recommended. Die die must try  at least once!

Fried chicken is the best thing on the menu - crispy and tender. The rice itself is actually not very flavorful at all. Other dishes like sotong and eggplant are fine. Was surprised that they sell San Pelligrino 😂 The food and drinks always takes such a long time to be served - not sure why this can't be improved, the faster we are served the faster they can turn the tables around. Longest queue time on weekends seems to be about 9.30am - 11am - no queue after that, so maybe better to go later.

This is one of the best Nasi Lemak in Town I would have to say and agree on talk of the town about this place. They serve the best and tasty nasi lemak. We went on weekdays and there were not many people queuing up but at the restaurant there was a huge crowd. We were able to get a table and their service was quite speedy as well. We ordered nasi lemak ayam berempah and nasi lemak ayam rendang. The ayam berempah fried chicken was juicy and tender where ayam rendang was also well cooked and very flavorful. The nasi lemak sambal was also full of flavor and not spicy where it can be enjoyed by most of the people at any age. I will definitely be coming back to have my nasi lemak here. You guys should try.

I only tried nasi lemak bec thats what they're famous of. Really worth it for those visiting KL
Food: nasi lemak is very good. You can really can taste savory in chicken and rice. Sambal is really good too. Traditionally its with boiled egg, but I think it will be at next level if its sunny side eggs. It was very satisfying meal and so I will try other dishes next time. Prices is very affordable.
Service: very basic. Waiting time to get order is around 10-15 mins, understandable because its a very busy store
Athmosphere: Its like your regular eat and go places, only that food is really good. Queue time takes about 15-20 mins in line during 1pm-3pm, not sure of the other hours. Its about 35-40mins from KLIA T1 at Sunday

We stopped by Village Park Restaurant in Damansara Utama PJ for lunch. It was so crowded and the queue was long but we waited patiently for a table. The fragrant smell of fried chicken welcomed us as we entered the restaurant. We were so hungry and decided to order a few plates of Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng Crispy, Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng Berempah and Singapore Mee Rebus to try. The fragrant rice was very fluffy and served with spicy sambal, hard boiled egg, fried anchovies, roasted peanuts and cucumber on the side. The fried chicken was well seasoned with spices and tasted flavourful. The whole plate of Nasi Lemak was so satisfying and made it a deliciously fulfilling meal for us. The Mee Rebus tasted good too. Overall, we enjoyed another delicious meal together with family!

formatted_address: 13, Jalan SS 3/37, Taman Universiti, 47300 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Botak Nasi Lemak

reviews.text:
They claim to be the 2nd Best in PJ.
Meaning ? Daring others to claim No. 1??

Rice has coconut fragrant n fried chicken drumstick was crispy outside n inside wet wet.
Sambal a bit bland maybe would be better if add a bit more sugar. Have some friend onions too.  Ikan bilis is crispy so as peanuts.

Saw a botak Chinese guy speak Cantonese in the preparation area. What Chinese Nasi Lemak??? I thought Nasi Lemak was Malays' staple.
This is by far the best coconut fragrant rice I have tasted.
There are Muslim workers and Muslim customers too.

I saw a Grab car that took more than 100 packs of nasi lemak for a customer. Plenty of Grab, Food Panda or Shopee rider.  Must be pretty good to have such a high delivery request.

Went to the restaurant after ordering delivery a few times. Simple layout with self service ordering. Tried the fried chicken with additional Squid sambal. Quite tasty, though in my opinion, not quite on par with the Village Park offering. The sambal was ok hut you have to pay if you want extra. The rice was fragrant enough but very little ikan bilis given. Overall, it pretty OK, better than average.

Visited here for lunch on Saturday, super tough to find parking.

Ordered nasi lemak with ayam goreng and added sambal sotong. Rice was slightly fragrant but small portion for me as a big eater. Sambal was more towards the sweet and spicy spectrum, went well with the rice. Fried chicken was hot and fresh, very juicy and tender! But the flavour is a bit bland to my liking, it would be even better if it is ayam goreng berempah. Nasi lemak came with complimentary whole egg, which is quite generous.

Price is pretty reasonable to me and the ambiance is nice, indoor and air conditioned so customers won’t be sweating after meal.

Very tasty Nasi Lemak served here... the rice is flavorful and the freshly fried chicken is so delicious.
One of the better Nasi Lemak restaurant in PJ.
Recommended.

One of the best nasi lemak spots in the Kelana Jaya neighborhood! The ayam goreng tastes great with crispy onions, and the sambal is nice and spicy. It's self-service, so head to the counter to order and pay.

formatted_address: 10, Jln 21/19, Sea Park Complex, Sea Park, 46300 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Botak Nasi Lemak (Sea Park)

reviews.text: The meehoon would have been better if it's warm. No dried shrimp taste in the meehoon siam. Sambal sotong is like sotong rojak as the sambal is poured over cooked cuttlefish. Nasi lemak was the best. Temps and taufu was ordinary I would have prefer a little crunch to it. Fried chicken was warm and crunchy. Rice has good santan flavour. Sambal lack kick and also flavour. Overall average food.

Just had a fantastic meal at Botak Nasi Lemak! The nasi lemak itself was fragrant and flavorful; the sambal was spicy and addictive.

The fried chicken was crispy and tasty, but unfortunately, it's a bit shy and needs a warm hug. If they could reheat it a bit more, it would be perfect. Would definitely recommend this place for a delicious and quick meal.

Fuyoh~Second Best Nasi Lemak in PJ? I’m doubt who dare to admit they are The Best Nasi lemak in PJ after Botak said they are second best. 😆

Anyhow, I think they are number 1 in My husband and his classmates heart. They one week came three times. Third time only bring me along. Unfair~ 🤣🤣🤣

Anyhow, after tried, hari- hari mau. Habislah~ no wonder My husband and his friends want to come here often.

Their nasi lemak Really fragrant. Sambal very Spicy. So be ready with a glass of water before you start to makan. If can, order their ice lemon tea. Not bad after you eating Spicy and drink it.

One point me and My husband must compliment will be their sambal sotong. I can tell you, I seldom eat sambal sotong nowaday. Because hard to find sedap punya sambal sotong. Semua overcooked and lembik. But Botak here cook very nice and chewy. You know what is Toi~ Toi~ ? That’s is the feeling when had My first Bite on sambal sotong. Delicious until I take away for My Sister. Highly recommended their sambal sotong.

By the way, even Chicken is cool, But the Chicken is fresh and juicy. And it is crunchy also. Now I know why they always come here, not to see botak, But eat Botak nasi lemak.  Apa boleh buat, I cannot botak, If not My husband will see me every day kan? 😜

I came to try this nasi lemak joint as they claimed they are 2nd best nasi lemak in PJ. Then I must come la. So service here is self service. Ordered from counter and you order your drink and pay at counter. (Service here I didn’t rate la).

So you have to wait to get your nasi lemak. You can choose from drumstick or thigh. You also can ask for more crispy onions. So my first bite the sambal gave me a kick then sweetness secondly. It’s quite good but spicy la. I wouldn’t suggest for more. Coz it’s too hot for me. Then the rice was fragrant and the chicken was fried perfectly and juicy. Overall I wouldn’t complain about it. Whether they have second best is still questionable as in my mind. Village and Bumbung which is near by are my top two. You come and try it yourself.

Had their mee goreng with ayam goreng as I don’t feel like having rice in the morning. Mee goreng is decent, and ayam goreng is crispy. The sambal is spicy and sweet kind. I would come here again to try their nasi lemak.

formatted_address: Jalan Sentosa 3/57, Pj Old Town, 46000 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Goreng Chef Fauzey

reviews.text: enjoyed it! highlight to me was the ayam goreng which IMHO is better than village park, burung hantu. the sambal and nasi goreng sambal were great too. pricing is great and big portions!
Personally it is overrated. The fried rice is just ready cooked and taste like standard Malay fried 🍚.

Delicious nasi lemak goreng with huge portion.
Really worth for ayam goreng set serve with large prawn.. definetely will get come again.
Can request also drink in bowl..

Pj old town must try the famous nasi lemak goreng with ayam goreng berempah & 1 prawn price only 9bug.
the nasi lemak goreng quite special &taste so delicious ..

still maintain 9 bug with big portion!(10/1/23)

Good Taste but not very impressive~
Got pass by can come and try the nasi lemak goreng, got "wok hey"

Very friendly price as the nasi lemak goreng with fried chicken and 1 prawn is RM 9 only~
How good if it serve with Telur Goreng~

Beverage here is quite good as well

formatted_address: Lot No C31,Concourse floor, Atria Mall, Jalan SS 22/23, Damansara Jaya, 47400 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Memang Best Noodle House

reviews.text:
The salted egg chicken nasi lemak was really just out of topic. Solid chicken breast, no flavour sauce except for it being salty...no salted egg flavour at all. Sad...

Nasi lemak xxl chicken, chicken lack seasoning and flavour. The size is huge but lack flavour. Interesting batter method, a little odd and interesting.

Anyway, it's not all bad. 3 star because noodles are okay.

Table and menu a little oil. Ambience and design nice and simple.

Price point, the usual commercial price point.

Staff, seems quite friendly.

Worth the try, you may like it. But not for me, rice meal is just a no no.

Ordered

Nasi lemak XXL & Nasi lemak rendang
The food portion is big and presentation is nice. similar to the picture shown in menu👍🏻 Gave generous portion of anchioves, peanuts and cucumber.

The nasi lemak is fragrant, XXL chicken is really crispy and whole chicken. Papadom is crispy 2 pieces.  Rendang chicken has a special herbs fragrant and i like it! However i dont really like the sambal for nasi lemak which has soury taste. Own preference is spicy sweet sambal.

After eating we immediately ordered another plate of food- meesiam to try😍 Again with the XXL Chicken.
Order a few items, surprisingly great presentation with delicious taste, Memang Best!!! They provide power bank for me to charge my mobile phone too :)) that’s the service quality we all love 😊

Love coming to this restaurant. Staff are friendly both on weekdays and weekends.
Food choices more than ak noodle at one utama. So certainly better if you have fussy ones in the family who doesn’t eat noodle.
Quality and taste - standard with ak noodle.

The shop runs some promotions during weekdays for students, which i find it good as they do not have enough time from school to tuition centers. Keep it up 👍🏻. Maybe have  cheaper deals for them.
Arrived around 10am on Friday. Ordering of food using QR Code. Nadhir was very helpful in assisting us to order. He was very patience with us to fix our requirements.

formatted_address: Lot 1.36.00, Level, 1, Pavilion Damansara Heights Rd, Pusat Bandar Damansara, 50490 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nalé The Nasi Lemak Company

reviews.text: Went here during office lunch hour on weekday.. The food appear just as the picture advertised on menu which impressive. We ordered nasi lemak rendang daging, nasi lemak goreng ayam, nasi kukus sambal hijau.. Everything is good and delicious. The rendang is so tender and the sambal hijau so sedap.. The chicken merely taste like chicken chop which it is, crispy and tender. The nasi lemak goreng taste like tasty nasi goreng cina hahha which is fine coz it still good.. Overall satisfied

Had lunch here recently with a friend who recommended the nasi lemak bakar. It came wrapped in leaves, suitably toasted, not burnt. The rice was ok, a bit compressed and lumpy, but still had the fragrance of coconut. Only wished they gave a bit more sambal inside the rice. The portion was very little. Maybe they were trying to get people to order extra sambal -- there were a few types available, including sambal hijau. The accompanying main dish ordered was the kerang petai in a green curry-type sauce. Must say it was creamy and quite tasty. In the end, are there better nasi lemak shops in PJ and KL? Yeah. But if you wanted a change of pace, Nale might be worth a try. They also have an interesting wagyu nasi lemak but at an eye-watering price. To be fair, it's a higher class cafe/restaurant so prices will match.

I have to say or admit,  NALE hits it. Best Nasi Lemak for me in Klang Valley. Delicious classic sambal unlimited(no add-on price) with varieties of add-on or ala carte dishes for you to choose. We love their ayam bakar and ayam goreng. Nasi lemak goreng also very delicious and they also serve just classic nasi lemak with no add on. Price is affordable, and I highly recommend nasi lemak lover to try it.

Had reservations of trying this atas nasi lemak shop and heard of its prices. But was really pleasantly surprised with the taste and unique flavours Nale served. Genuinely the prices are of average KL prices. Great place to bring visiting travellers to try nasi lemak in a nice air conditioned restaurant.

Heard so much positive reviews of this atas Nasi lemak.

Went on a Sunday and not much crowd, probably cos it’s in a quiet shopping mall.

Had the Nasi lemak Ayam Goreng and Ayam Bakar.
Both are really good, especially when pairing with the Nale sauce.
A different take on classic Nasi lemak !

Also order Gulai Sayur and Lekor which were good too.

Waiting time was abit long despite the not being crowded

formatted_address: No 2, Jalan 51a/223, Seksyen 51a, 46100 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Panas 223

reviews.text: One of the finest Nasi Lemak experiences I've had. The restaurant remains open until 1:30 AM, ensuring that you can enjoy freshly prepared, piping hot Nasi Lemak even late into the night. The beef, in particular, is exceptional, rich in flavor and cooked to perfection.

Ah, Nasi Lemak Panas 223 – a treasure trove of flavors nestled within the heart of a bustling food haven. Here, the aroma of freshly cooked nasi lemak mingles with the morning air, enticing even the weariest soul to pause and savor a taste of Malaysia’s beloved comfort food. Each spoonful is a delight, as the rice, warm and fragrant, pairs seamlessly with the sambal – a careful balance of sweet, spicy, and tangy that stirs the senses awake.

And then, there is the ayam goreng – crispy on the outside, tender within, each bite a reminder of the simple joys of a well-prepared meal. The taste here is honest, unpretentious, yet deeply satisfying. One feels the dedication in every element of the plate, crafted not with grandeur but with genuine care.

The staff, too, mirror the warmth of the place, serving with a smile that feels genuine and true. They are ever-helpful, eager to ensure that each visitor leaves content and comforted. Amidst the liveliness of the many stalls surrounding it, Nasi Lemak Panas 223 stands out not merely for its food, but for the experience it offers – a glimpse into a cherished Malaysian tradition.

Nasi Lemak Paru was delicious with good portions. The paru is still crispy and the rice is fragrant. Their sambal however was sweet and spicy. People who have low tolerance for spicy foods may find it spicy.

Unrelated to this shop, but this Medan selera is quite hot and stuffy during the day.

Ordered via Grabfood. After clarification with the rider, the shop turned out forgetting to put the sambal in the nasi lemak. Luckily I was able to get a refund from Grab but seriously, nasi lemak with no sambal are you kidding me? Also I realised the shop is downgrading lately…
Nasi lemak kerang sambal & hard boiled egg , 2nd plate nasi lemak with hard boiled egg, dry sotong and tempe , both cost RM22. Not worth to pay for the price

formatted_address: 27M, (1st Floor, Jalan SS 21/37, Damansara Utama, 47400 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Mamalee Nasi Lemak

reviews.text:
My colleagues brought me to Mama Lee for lunch earlier, and I decided to try the Nasi Lemak with Buttermilk Fried Chicken. The fried chicken was a huge, crispy piece, perfectly seasoned with a rich, fragrant aroma. The buttermilk sauce was spot on -creamy and incredibly appetizing when mixed with the rice. The drink taste was just average (I ordered Teh C) for me.

I have to agree with the other comments: if you’re not up for queuing at VP, this is a great alternative. It was quite crowded even during lunch on a regular workday, so it’s clearly a popular spot.

Located on 1st floor. Luckily easy to find with good signage. Parked at Starling mall and walk across about 5 mins to get here. Same row as hsbc.

Really enjoyed Nasi Lemak.  Crispy, tender and big piece of chicken Maryland.  Rich buttermilk (would be better if given more sauce). What I like best is their sambal.  Sambal has nice aroma and right amount of chili. Superb ! A bit pricey about rm18/plate so luckily taste yummy. Enjoyed it.

Very generous food portion. The food is flavourful! If you have small stomach like me order the rendang RM13 one and not the rm16 buttermilk one. I struggled. 10/10 would come again (if got parking lol)
Loved it. Tasty nasi lemak. Huge portion and L shape chicken so fresh and crunchy. Order buttermilk sauce nasi lemak fried chicken for RM16
This place is so underrated but the quality of the food is beyond expectation. The best part is...you don't need to queue to eat a good nasi lemak (if you know...u know 😉). The delivery is fast.

formatted_address: G(E)-013, MIDVALLEY MEGAMALL, Lingkaran Syed Putra, Mid Valley City, 59200 Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: NALÉ - The Nasi Lemak Company

reviews.text: Nale offers delicious, freshly prepared meals with a variety of flavors to suit all tastes. The portions are satisfying, and the quality of ingredients really stands out. The service is quick and friendly, making it a great spot for a casual meal or takeaway. Highly recommended for anyone looking for tasty, no-fuss food!”

Nasi lemak ayam goreng Nale - RM 21.90

Recommend to upgrade your Nasi lemak to bakar extra RM 2

It would have been nice if the food is delivered hot.

Will come back for this - Nasi lemak bakar klasik @ RM 11.90 only

Very busy during lunch hour.

Sign-up for RM 5 voucher & a free drink 🤭

Quite surprised that the food here is pretty good.
What I enjoyed most is the Ayam Bakar with Nasi Goreng.
Their Nale sauce is quite unique and tasty.
Beef were all cooked pretty well, soft and tender.
Ayam Goreng is okay, crispy and juicy as well.
What I did not enjoy was the Indomee, quite bland, so it’s not a good combo for their food.
Lekor is okay, not that tasty tho.
Brinjal fried were not bad, crispy and tasty.

First time seeing Indo mee priced at RM289—wow, that was a shocker! But we decided to try their nasi lemak with ayam bakar and the Indo mee with ayam bakar.

The nasi lemak was absolutely worth it—fragrant rice with tasty sambal and kuah. Every bite was delicious and worth every cent. Highly recommend trying it!

As for the Indo mee, that was my mistake for ordering it at a nasi lemak restaurant. The noodles arrived a bit cold, and the soft-boiled egg was also cold, which made it less enjoyable. Thankfully, the sambal helped me finish it.

One area for improvement is their table numbering system. Staff often seemed to search for table numbers, which could cause delays and make food arrive colder. Fixing table numbers would save time and keep food hot for customers.

Prices here are on the higher side, especially for food and drinks. Would I come back? Yes, but only for the nasi lemak! 😄

one of the best nasi lemak i can get in mid valley. the grilled chicken is my fav! the gravy/sauce tastes damn good. the price is a little bit pricey but i think its worth it. the indoor seating feels cozy and comfortable but the outside seems to be a little bit crowded during lunch time.

formatted_address: 39, Jalan 52/18, Pj New Town, 46200 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Daun Pisang Kak Dee

reviews.text: Simple, no fuss nasi lemak that tastes like home cooked food. There's a variety of add on like cockles, fried chicken, sambal chicken, fried egg. Kak Dee is a hardworking, lovely person who always makes us feel welcome. Service is top notch.

Memang nice nasi lemak with your choice of chicken or succulent beef in the most sedap sauce! The place also offers nasi melayu and roti canai.

Reasonably priced and outstanding nasi lemak (RM4.50 for daging); roti is a bit doughy but passable. The place is crowded so you'll probably have to share share tables lah.

Staff are friendly and the place is mostly cleanish. Heh.

Not the best tasting nasi lemak (rice and added on lala portion quite small), and the coffee was too sweet and not strong enough for me. But the shop was very clean, friendly staff/lady boss, and there was a lot of nice natural light and air in the morning. Will come back for brunch/lunch (starts at 10pm) to try their Malay nasi campur (mix rice).

Food is great. However service is suck. This only came from akk yang menjual nasi lemak upfront. People coming for buying. Not begger. She acting not want to sell, no manner. Love to eat the nasi lemak however not anymore
Got attracted by the que to the stall, looks pretty decent however taste ordinary... I bet a yummy ones will be able to take over the que unless it improves.....

formatted_address: 8, Jalan Raja Muda Musa, Kampung Baru, 50300 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Wanjo Kampung Baru

reviews.text:
Decided to give it a try as Wanjo is one of the top rated nasi lemak.

According to my friend, this outlet underwent renovation as initially, it was a small shop. The white color made the shop looked spacious, cleaner + the table arrangements were organized 👍 There was also air-conditioned eating space where diners have to pay RM 1/head. Fret not as it has QR code for cashless payment, too.

Despite listed as a must-try nasi lemak, personally I have opposite opinions.
- The rice is lacked of rasa lemak + the portion was little
- The sambal was sweet 😵😵😵 Sambal SHOULD BE SAVOURY, not sweet. If you love eating sweet sambal, this is the one for you. Its sweetness turned off my mood 😌
- The price for a plain nasi lemak, I repeat, PLAIN nasi lemak, was ridiculous 🤯🤯🤯 For the price of RM 3.20, I could get a nasi lemak tepi jalan complete with its anchovies, cucumbers, nuts + sambal.

However, the paru was nice - not so crunchy + chewy.

Will I repeat? High probably 🙅‍♀️ unless the sambal is no longer sweet (according to my friend too, sambal dahulu didn't taste like this) + the price is realistic. Apologies for being honest as I found it overrated 🙏

A famous Nasi Lemak in KL, the line is always long but the service is fast. Their place is huge and also clean. The choices of their ‘lauk’ is so various but their fried chicken is always a must for you to pick

They also have another lauk such as rendang, paru, kerang, etc and side dish such as perkedel, tempe, etc. Their drinks comes in a big jar and of course, an ice tea in KL always a must to order. They also provide a dispenser for you to have free mineral water. You can also order their juices, comes in many choices, big portion and fresh fruits.

Their price are so cheap, i only spent less that 50RM for 4 persons. Go try it!

Each time I visit KL, I make it a point to stop by this renowned Nasi Lemak. During my last visit, while the food quality wasn't exceptional, it was still enjoyable. I do hope they can maintain a more consistent standard in the future, as they once did. On weekends or public holidays, the venue tends to be crowded, but the staff is attentive and will assist in finding a table

My recent visit to Nasi Lemak Wanjo was okay overall. The nasi lemak itself was decent—fragrant rice, well-balanced sambal, and tasty sides like the ayam masak merah and rendang. However, the experience was let down by the service. The staff seemed a bit lazy and inattentive, which took away from what could have been a more enjoyable meal. Hopefully, they'll step up their game next time.

Nasi Lemak’s the best place in KL. Heard about its reputation but still highly surprise when I visit. Great atmosphere of local surroundings makes me feel like I am really in Malaysia. The more, the food is great. Tasty sambal and crispy Ayam goreng was also great. Will recommend to friends.

formatted_address: 8, Jalan Raja Muda Musa, Kampung Baru, 50300 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Wanjo Kampung Baru

reviews.text:
Decided to give it a try as Wanjo is one of the top rated nasi lemak.

According to my friend, this outlet underwent renovation as initially, it was a small shop. The white color made the shop looked spacious, cleaner + the table arrangements were organized 👍 There was also air-conditioned eating space where diners have to pay RM 1/head. Fret not as it has QR code for cashless payment, too.

Despite listed as a must-try nasi lemak, personally I have opposite opinions.
- The rice is lacked of rasa lemak + the portion was little
- The sambal was sweet 😵😵😵 Sambal SHOULD BE SAVOURY, not sweet. If you love eating sweet sambal, this is the one for you. Its sweetness turned off my mood 😌
- The price for a plain nasi lemak, I repeat, PLAIN nasi lemak, was ridiculous 🤯🤯🤯 For the price of RM 3.20, I could get a nasi lemak tepi jalan complete with its anchovies, cucumbers, nuts + sambal.

However, the paru was nice - not so crunchy + chewy.

Will I repeat? High probably 🙅‍♀️ unless the sambal is no longer sweet (according to my friend too, sambal dahulu didn't taste like this) + the price is realistic. Apologies for being honest as I found it overrated 🙏

A famous Nasi Lemak in KL, the line is always long but the service is fast. Their place is huge and also clean. The choices of their ‘lauk’ is so various but their fried chicken is always a must for you to pick

They also have another lauk such as rendang, paru, kerang, etc and side dish such as perkedel, tempe, etc. Their drinks comes in a big jar and of course, an ice tea in KL always a must to order. They also provide a dispenser for you to have free mineral water. You can also order their juices, comes in many choices, big portion and fresh fruits.

Their price are so cheap, i only spent less that 50RM for 4 persons. Go try it!

Each time I visit KL, I make it a point to stop by this renowned Nasi Lemak. During my last visit, while the food quality wasn't exceptional, it was still enjoyable. I do hope they can maintain a more consistent standard in the future, as they once did. On weekends or public holidays, the venue tends to be crowded, but the staff is attentive and will assist in finding a table

My recent visit to Nasi Lemak Wanjo was okay overall. The nasi lemak itself was decent—fragrant rice, well-balanced sambal, and tasty sides like the ayam masak merah and rendang. However, the experience was let down by the service. The staff seemed a bit lazy and inattentive, which took away from what could have been a more enjoyable meal. Hopefully, they'll step up their game next time.

Nasi Lemak’s the best place in KL. Heard about its reputation but still highly surprise when I visit. Great atmosphere of local surroundings makes me feel like I am really in Malaysia. The more, the food is great. Tasty sambal and crispy Ayam goreng was also great. Will recommend to friends.

formatted_address: G(E)-013, MIDVALLEY MEGAMALL, Lingkaran Syed Putra, Mid Valley City, 59200 Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: NALÉ - The Nasi Lemak Company

reviews.text: Nale offers delicious, freshly prepared meals with a variety of flavors to suit all tastes. The portions are satisfying, and the quality of ingredients really stands out. The service is quick and friendly, making it a great spot for a casual meal or takeaway. Highly recommended for anyone looking for tasty, no-fuss food!”

Nasi lemak ayam goreng Nale - RM 21.90

Recommend to upgrade your Nasi lemak to bakar extra RM 2

It would have been nice if the food is delivered hot.

Will come back for this - Nasi lemak bakar klasik @ RM 11.90 only

Very busy during lunch hour.

Sign-up for RM 5 voucher & a free drink 🤭

Quite surprised that the food here is pretty good.
What I enjoyed most is the Ayam Bakar with Nasi Goreng.
Their Nale sauce is quite unique and tasty.
Beef were all cooked pretty well, soft and tender.
Ayam Goreng is okay, crispy and juicy as well.
What I did not enjoy was the Indomee, quite bland, so it’s not a good combo for their food.
Lekor is okay, not that tasty tho.
Brinjal fried were not bad, crispy and tasty.

First time seeing Indo mee priced at RM289—wow, that was a shocker! But we decided to try their nasi lemak with ayam bakar and the Indo mee with ayam bakar.

The nasi lemak was absolutely worth it—fragrant rice with tasty sambal and kuah. Every bite was delicious and worth every cent. Highly recommend trying it!

As for the Indo mee, that was my mistake for ordering it at a nasi lemak restaurant. The noodles arrived a bit cold, and the soft-boiled egg was also cold, which made it less enjoyable. Thankfully, the sambal helped me finish it.

One area for improvement is their table numbering system. Staff often seemed to search for table numbers, which could cause delays and make food arrive colder. Fixing table numbers would save time and keep food hot for customers.

Prices here are on the higher side, especially for food and drinks. Would I come back? Yes, but only for the nasi lemak! 😄

one of the best nasi lemak i can get in mid valley. the grilled chicken is my fav! the gravy/sauce tastes damn good. the price is a little bit pricey but i think its worth it. the indoor seating feels cozy and comfortable but the outside seems to be a little bit crowded during lunch time.

formatted_address: Lot 1.36.00, Level, 1, Pavilion Damansara Heights Rd, Pusat Bandar Damansara, 50490 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nalé The Nasi Lemak Company

reviews.text: Went here during office lunch hour on weekday.. The food appear just as the picture advertised on menu which impressive. We ordered nasi lemak rendang daging, nasi lemak goreng ayam, nasi kukus sambal hijau.. Everything is good and delicious. The rendang is so tender and the sambal hijau so sedap.. The chicken merely taste like chicken chop which it is, crispy and tender. The nasi lemak goreng taste like tasty nasi goreng cina hahha which is fine coz it still good.. Overall satisfied

Had lunch here recently with a friend who recommended the nasi lemak bakar. It came wrapped in leaves, suitably toasted, not burnt. The rice was ok, a bit compressed and lumpy, but still had the fragrance of coconut. Only wished they gave a bit more sambal inside the rice. The portion was very little. Maybe they were trying to get people to order extra sambal -- there were a few types available, including sambal hijau. The accompanying main dish ordered was the kerang petai in a green curry-type sauce. Must say it was creamy and quite tasty. In the end, are there better nasi lemak shops in PJ and KL? Yeah. But if you wanted a change of pace, Nale might be worth a try. They also have an interesting wagyu nasi lemak but at an eye-watering price. To be fair, it's a higher class cafe/restaurant so prices will match.

I have to say or admit,  NALE hits it. Best Nasi Lemak for me in Klang Valley. Delicious classic sambal unlimited(no add-on price) with varieties of add-on or ala carte dishes for you to choose. We love their ayam bakar and ayam goreng. Nasi lemak goreng also very delicious and they also serve just classic nasi lemak with no add on. Price is affordable, and I highly recommend nasi lemak lover to try it.

Had reservations of trying this atas nasi lemak shop and heard of its prices. But was really pleasantly surprised with the taste and unique flavours Nale served. Genuinely the prices are of average KL prices. Great place to bring visiting travellers to try nasi lemak in a nice air conditioned restaurant.

Heard so much positive reviews of this atas Nasi lemak.

Went on a Sunday and not much crowd, probably cos it’s in a quiet shopping mall.

Had the Nasi lemak Ayam Goreng and Ayam Bakar.
Both are really good, especially when pairing with the Nale sauce.
A different take on classic Nasi lemak !

Also order Gulai Sayur and Lekor which were good too.

Waiting time was abit long despite the not being crowded

formatted_address: Changkat Bukit Bintang, Bukit Bintang, 50200 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Alor Corner

reviews.text:
The queue quite long even before they start business. About 20 to 30 people ahead of me, took about 15 minutes untill my turn to serve. I thought to give 3 star for the food but the Nasi too soft and sotong also too soft and bland.
The price is not too expensive if compared to restaurants but slightly higher compare to gerai tepi jalan...
Overall is ok just overrated, Most of the nasi lemak shop or gerai also can beat it.

#NasiLemakSotong RM10.00
#NasiLemak #NasiLemakAlorCorner

Actually I can say this is ordinary, not so special but also not bad at all.
It's a good place to grab a quick meal around Alor street, with super reasonable price.
We ate here paying only RM 15 for 2 persons, with additional chicken not in the picture, so yes it's very cheap.

If you want to try, come early in the morning as it sells out quick.

This is trully a gem! Super delicious nasi lemak for breakfast and lunch. Everything mix really well. The rice, chicken, egg, sotong and especially the sambal. Nice!  This probably will be our top priority breakfast while in KL.

The best low cost nasi lemak located in the famous street. The portion is a bit big and the taste is good. Currently  there is no table to dine in, so you can sit on the stairs near the food stall or go to Nasi Kandar Ar Rizziq to dine in (but you must order at least their drinks to dine in).

Nasi lemak ayam RM9
Nasi lemak telur + perkedel RM9

Also, do not forget to try Cham Tarik drink in front of this stall. It is so delicious Kopi-Teh Tarik.

Tiktok viral Nasi Lemak (Malaysian traditional mixed rice). Queueing up to 30 minutes. Delicious meal with lot choices of toppings. Open from 7am till finish, but don't try your luck, get there early.

formatted_address: 128, Jalan Pahang, Titiwangsa Sentral, 53000 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: NASI LEMAK BETIS KAMBING KL

reviews.text: The Lambshank set was worth it.. huggeee size (refer picture).. menu selection consist of true Malay cuisine (Nasi kerabu, lontong, nasi lemak, mee kari etc.) So the place is great to bring tourists to try our food 👍🏻

🚶mpromptu Lunch 🤷
Greeted & briefeed by 4renly 🚶 staff.
Lontong Darat Paru Berlada 🍲 is a MUST TRY for Lontong lovers 😎
And bet most of thier dishes are yummylicious 😋😎
Definately will let them flyer goes 🔥😱
And yeah am glad🚶 come across this new (2 week Opening) and surely will comeback for more 😋😎
Food was tasty. Place was clean. One of the best sambals around. Good job guys. Keep up the good and clean job.
First time i've been here. Satisfied with the food! Nasi Ambeng so much delicious +  teh tarik. Will come again and want to try their other signature menus.

I had the pleasure of dining at this restaurant together with my friends and I must say the food was absolutely delicious!
Every dish was thoughtfully prepared and full of flavour.
The owner was exceptionally friendly and went out of his way to ensure that we were comfortable and satisfied with our meal. His warmth made the experience even more enjoyable.

I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great food and a welcoming atmosphere. I can’t wait to come back and try more items on their menu. This spot is definitely a hidden gem!

formatted_address: 19, Jalan 14/27b, Desa Setapak, 53300 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Together Nasi Lemak 毅启香米椰浆饭

html_attributions: Together Nasi Lemak 毅启香米椰浆饭

reviews.text: I’ve tried their XL fried chicken legs before and became a regular customer. It’s a great improvement that they switched to boneless chicken legs, and they’ve also started offering fried pork belly. After trying it once, I wanted to eat it again! It’s awesome and the price is quite cheap in KL! I hope they open more branches so I can eat there more easily. 👍

If compare to the other pork Nasi lemak. This one is best so far. Fried pork belly was good. Rice is fragrant with strong santan flavour. Curry pork so so. Sotong ok. Sambal ok. Generous portions. Kopitiam old. Just makan and go. Keep it up.

The pork berempah is ok and price is reasonable/ cheap . The sotong i personally dont recommend. Their nasi lemak sambal ia just so-so.
Can try if you dont mind the long queue.
1 thing that i like is their *manual queue system*

Personal view: overrated

waiting time was way too long during our visit because staff was acting very very slow. there were about 5 customers in front of us and they bought one or at most two packs per person, but it took more than half an hour until our turn to order. meat was cold thus became hard, so we couldn’t enjoy to the max.

Recommend delicious Nasi Lemak
✅Crispy & Spicy fried chicken (boneless)
✅Non-spicy berempah pork with crispy shredded coconut

Especially sambal must try, for me is standard spicy. Worth it👍🏻

formatted_address: 8, Jln Seri Rejang 5, Setapak Jaya, 53300 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Saleha

reviews.text:
The first time we arrived here, we expected only a row of normal shoplot, apparently it is a shop located in a small factory that is usually used as a small industry such as a car workshop or a welding workshop, well done to Nasi Lemak Saleha.
Review on the dishes, the sambal nasi lemak is their signature & trademark. Variety of breakfast menu such as nasi lemak ayam goreng rempah, ayam rendang, paru goreng dan sotong sambal, lontong, fried kuey teow and also toasted bread and kuih-muih.
Parking is free but limited due to there's a Pasar Tani nearby.
Try by yourself & you would't regret.

Nasi Lemak: 5/5 - Fragrant coconut rice with just the right balance of flavor.

Sambal: 5/5 - Spicy, tangy, and packed with depth, complementing the dish perfectly.

Every element was delicious and offered a unique twist, unlike any other Nasi Lemak I’ve had before. I’m definitely coming back to explore more of the menu!

First time here in Setapak😅 wanted to try Ayam Goreng but the Abang waiter said finish already 😢 Maybe they can serve more Ayam goreng in future but overall, all good.. you should try and taste it by your own 😊

The restaurant offers small portions (but its good 🥹 delicious) at a high price, and while the interior is clean, the front area has some water trash that can be unpleasant if you sit at the front of the restaurant; and, parking can be challenging when it's crowded.

You would rarely get dissapointed with nasi lemak, but sadly its the case here. Sambal was tasteless, chicken too aged (ayam lama) and dry. Nasi lemak nothing to talk about. We order half boiled eggs and it came small plastic cup. The busker was too loud you can barely hear the person next to you talking. This place has all the makings of a restaurant that does not care about the food, just the profit. The most mediocre nasi lemak ayam goreng here cost 13.50. Take your money elsewhere so you wont be dissapointed.

formatted_address: 6, Jalan 21/11b, Sea Park, 46300 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Bumbung

reviews.text: The place is so easy to find and it’s located in between the shop lots. The shop opens until 12 am but they open till 12:30 am since some customers come late. Just one request for the customers, please go there before 12 am since the workers also need to do their closing and back home. One of the craving nasi lemak in KL and it’s really taste good. They also have Burnt Cheesecake and Mango Stick Rice as an extra menus. Must try nasi Lemak and thank me later.

The place was very crowded at night, and I had to wait in line for a few minutes. I tried the nasi lemak ayam goreng for RM 8, and it was quite tasty. It's a great spot for nighttime dining with an open space.

Nasi lemak with fried egg and fried chicken cost RM8. Nasi has 'lemak' taste.. Chicken was slightly hard and sambal was not one of the best. However, the fried meehoon was good. Was not dry n had tomatoes which gave it both a savoury, spicy from the chili and sweet / sour from the tomatoes. Rendang chicken was alright too.

Dnt know how long ago was my last visit. Came here on a Monday night and didn't need to wait for a table which was nice.

This time round- I didn't wanna have their nasi lemak, I went for the Maggie goreng and it was satisfying. Good flavor. Somehow they cut the noodle into shorter length:') other than that, not bad at all!

The fried chicken is nice especially the outer layer, somehow the meat didn't felt like the spice went in. It was moist though.

I've been a frequent visitor for the past 20 years. I've always liked their food . Started off with indo Mee and today they've got varieties and even started with a POS system to collect payment from customers. I used to admire all their staff's super quick maths during the "boss Kira" time. Their service is really fast and accurate most of the time. In terms of cleanliness you can't expect much because your seating areas are between road alleys. Honestly the drain and cockroaches freaks me out. Other than that this place brings me back to my teenage days. I will only order their indo Mee and Milo Ais and that's the best.

formatted_address: G10, Oasis Business Center BU4, Changkat Bandar Utama, Bandar Utama, 47800 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: nasi lemak shop.

reviews.text:
Amazing nasi lemak spot in Bandar Utama! This place is so popular that there’s always a queue, but it’s absolutely worth the wait. The restaurant is modern, clean, and the service is impressively quick. The food? Simply delicious!

The nasi lemak with fried chicken was a standout — the sambal was perfectly balanced, and the crispy chicken skin added an irresistible crunch. The mee siam was another winner, packed with flavor. Don’t miss the kaya toast — rich, creamy, and the perfect sweet treat to round out the meal.

Highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great food and a welcoming atmosphere. I’ll definitely be back!

I am not a connoisseur of Nasi Lemak, but this place is a good option to get an interesting experience of this popular dish.
It’s usually crowded during lunch, so you might need to plan ahead.
The service is good and people there are nice.

I went here after this place was the talk of the town. I heard they are serving the best nasi lemak. Unfortunately, the nasi lemak was just below average. Nothing to hype about to be honest. The sambal is honestly tasteless for us and don't have the umphh at all. The fried chicken was moderate like 5/10 rating as I have eaten the best fried chicken at some other places. Portion wise it's normal serving for an adult. Price wise I felt it's a little expensive but okay to try once. The atmosphere was unpleasant where the tables are too close to one another which is quite uncomfortable. You guys could try once as our taste buds are not the same.

Long queue and large crowd during lunch hour but the restaurant did well to accommodate people while queueing with having a large tent with air cooler and seats also providing drinks and snack while waiting. Staff is helpful and friendly.

Restaurant have outdoor seats along the corridor and indoor with a long bar table and tables seat but little bit tight space due to space of restaurant not too big.

We had the Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng, Mee Siam Curry Chicken and lemon barley.
The rice have slight coconut fragrance aroma while the sambal spiciness and sweetness just nice and balance. The highlight would be the ayam goreng with just fried freshly and hot. Chicken meat is tender and juicy with skin is crispy with well marinated rempah. Plenty of crispy fried rempah given on top.
Mee Siam is delicious and curry chicken is flavourful with thick and heavy curry. Portion of curry chicken and potatoes also generous.
Lemon barley surprise us as it is not those sweet with syrup type. Plenty of barley on the bottom with slight lemon aroma in it.

Definitely one of best nasi lemak I had.

The Nasi Lemak berempah is really yummy, fragrant rice and tasty crispy chicken.
White curry noodles is nice, quite lemak and the sambal sotong is a good addition.
Prawn noodles was so so, not that special.
Dry mee siam is tasty as well, quite tasty, with the curry chicken.

formatted_address: 1, Jalan Daud, Kampung Baru, 50300 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Kak Chuk

reviews.text: Nasi lemak taste in a sweet side. I had Nasi Lemak Sotong cost RM8. Drink is self service RM2. Taste is fine, a big portion and have kangkung. Honest from me not the best Nasi Lemak since the rice doesn’t taste the coconut too much maybe for that day. But it walking distance from Hospital Kg Baru got place to park nearby.

Most underrated Nasi Lemak in town. The sambal is so good and delicious. They said the sambal like orang lama2 cook. like the beef rendang and also sambal sotong. Surely will repeat! The unique is the kangkung. All the combinations will give you perfect taste. Have limited place because the they open the table a few. But the atmosphere you feel like eat at Malay villages. Very recommended place for Nasi Lemak fans.
long queue but worth wait, sambal is flavourful, paru is unique not typical crispy type.

Good food especially the nasi lemak, rendang chicken and the sambal. The eggs are good. The sambal is not spicy. Everything is great. There is even a view of the landmark of Malaysia, KLCC at the opposite of the road.

I think the reason why people keep coming is because of their portion. For me, a small portion makes you crave for more. But their nasi lemak was soooo damn huge (3 scoops of rice). Sadly, the rice tasted like plain rice and was quite dry but the sambal wins my heart. The taste was balanced between spicy, sweet and sour. Spiciness is low to medium. The fried anchovies were too salty. All in all, just a suggestion from me, please add more santan, halba and shallot in your nasi, reduce the portion and please soak the anchovies first before frying, it will make it less salty and crispier. Price wise was okay, when compared with the portion. And please come early, because there will be a line to queue before you can enjoy your nasi lemak.

formatted_address: 5, Jalan SS 21/37, Damansara Utama, 47400 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Village Park Restaurant

reviews.text:
This place is super popular with locals and tourists, dine in and takeaways also.

Outside the eatery are neatly arranged rows of chairs  fully occupied by food delivery riders waiting for their pick ups.

Needless to say, food is good, service is systematic and efficient.

Highly recommended. Die die must try  at least once!

Fried chicken is the best thing on the menu - crispy and tender. The rice itself is actually not very flavorful at all. Other dishes like sotong and eggplant are fine. Was surprised that they sell San Pelligrino 😂 The food and drinks always takes such a long time to be served - not sure why this can't be improved, the faster we are served the faster they can turn the tables around. Longest queue time on weekends seems to be about 9.30am - 11am - no queue after that, so maybe better to go later.

This is one of the best Nasi Lemak in Town I would have to say and agree on talk of the town about this place. They serve the best and tasty nasi lemak. We went on weekdays and there were not many people queuing up but at the restaurant there was a huge crowd. We were able to get a table and their service was quite speedy as well. We ordered nasi lemak ayam berempah and nasi lemak ayam rendang. The ayam berempah fried chicken was juicy and tender where ayam rendang was also well cooked and very flavorful. The nasi lemak sambal was also full of flavor and not spicy where it can be enjoyed by most of the people at any age. I will definitely be coming back to have my nasi lemak here. You guys should try.

I only tried nasi lemak bec thats what they're famous of. Really worth it for those visiting KL
Food: nasi lemak is very good. You can really can taste savory in chicken and rice. Sambal is really good too. Traditionally its with boiled egg, but I think it will be at next level if its sunny side eggs. It was very satisfying meal and so I will try other dishes next time. Prices is very affordable.
Service: very basic. Waiting time to get order is around 10-15 mins, understandable because its a very busy store
Athmosphere: Its like your regular eat and go places, only that food is really good. Queue time takes about 15-20 mins in line during 1pm-3pm, not sure of the other hours. Its about 35-40mins from KLIA T1 at Sunday

We stopped by Village Park Restaurant in Damansara Utama PJ for lunch. It was so crowded and the queue was long but we waited patiently for a table. The fragrant smell of fried chicken welcomed us as we entered the restaurant. We were so hungry and decided to order a few plates of Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng Crispy, Nasi Lemak Ayam Goreng Berempah and Singapore Mee Rebus to try. The fragrant rice was very fluffy and served with spicy sambal, hard boiled egg, fried anchovies, roasted peanuts and cucumber on the side. The fried chicken was well seasoned with spices and tasted flavourful. The whole plate of Nasi Lemak was so satisfying and made it a deliciously fulfilling meal for us. The Mee Rebus tasted good too. Overall, we enjoyed another delicious meal together with family!

formatted_address: No 868, 5, Jalan Sultan, Township, 50000 City, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Famous Fried Rice (Ray Power Corner)

reviews.text: Cool place. I had the chicken bihun goreng. It was very flavorful and had a great texture. The kitchen staff made it just a little spicy upon request, as I had a bit of a dodgy tummy at the time. I loved my dish. My husband ordered the butter chicken. He thought it was going to be more like the Indian butter chicken, and it is not. It has more of a corn chowder/actual butter flavor. It was fine! Tasted good! Just know it’s also a Malaysian dish if you’re unfamiliar. Staff were all very kind, they play loud 90s club music. Seating is outdoor and can be a little hot.

Amazing food, we got the Singapore noodles  and kam heong (both very nice) It was served with beaming slimes from the waitress and staff. The street atmosphere was very enjoyable and I would definitely go back.

The staffs were nice but the food was just awful. This is probably the worst food i’ve had during my 6 day vacation in Kuala Lumpur.

I ordered the following:
- Claims, RM 20
- Hokkien Mee, RM 10
- Lemon Iced Tea, RM 6
- Beef Satay (5), RM 12.5

90% of the claims shells were empty and some were even filled with dirt. It was drenched in so much sauce that i couldn’t taste anything but the sweetness from the sauce.

The same goes for the Hokkien Mee, hardly any noodle and loaded with sweet sauce. The noodle strands were all broken up.

The satay was OK but not great. i’ve had better.

Overall, this place has tourist trap vibes written all over it. They sell Chinese food but everyone here is indian. The customers are also westerners or Indians.

Raymond is a master chef!
The best vegan food I’ve had on this planet, I’m from UK, London born and bred, so the there’s no shortage of vegan alternatives in the 8 years I’ve been vegan. Travelled the globe, but this place, veggie, vegan or not, you MUST travel to Kuala Lumpur and try this if you’re stumbling across this now. Affordable, honest & insanely great food! Thanks to Raymond the chef & the team, manager was amazing & a beautiful server too. Very helpful & easy to eat multiple dishes & drinks with ease :) thanks for the experience. Good music too, in a hot country city centre, the music & breezy theme with the water & hanging decorations make this such a gorgeous place to eat. High quality cheffing & tasty cuisine.

I had an amazing experience at this place.The flavors of the Malaysian street food were authentic and absolutely incredible. Each dish was a burst of spices and aromas that transported me straight to the streets of Malaysia. The ambiance was cozy, and the staff were friendly and attentive. Whether you're craving something savoury, chilly or sweet , this place has it all. Highly recommend to anyone looking for an unforgettable culinary adventure!

formatted_address: Pasar Batu 2 1/2 Ipoh, Jln Sultan Azlan Shah, Sentul, 51200 Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Angah

reviews.text: Seller friendly and accommodating. Engaging in small talk, the seller made us feel welcomed and comfortable, even inquiring about any allergies we may have. Portion size of their nasi lemak were generous, the prices reasonable, and their drinks were delicious, Prepared with a bartender's style and topped with foam. We will definitely return to try out other items on the menu.

We came here early morning after KL Car Free and was lucky that the queue was not that long at the time. Mind you that you need to secure your table first since it's an open seating.

The process of ordering is smooth, the worker is attentive. The price for me is quite reasonable considering it's hard to find nowadays a complete Nasi Lemak in KL with complete ingredients.

The nasi lemak taste good for me, the sambal a bit on sweeter side but keep a bit of a spice kick too, the kangkung and ikan bilis is quite a good quality. The roti bakar can be quite slow to arrive, so you might want to consider not ordering that
during peak hours.

The drink especially great to me with quite a good price for that kind of quality. Love the calamansi drink and the drink maker can be quite a sight to see for his 'bartender' skills.

Overall, will definitely come back here for breakfast (of course during off peak time).

We went to road to UNESCO - manage to only try nasi lemak 223 and angah. I was really excited for 223 cause I ate it all the time during college days and I remember or I thought it was good. Sorry 223, y’all don’t stand a chance next to Nasi Lemak angah. angah’s rice, Sambal, kangkung, tempeh…. Sedapppp

The place is very welcoming, the staff is very amicable and friendly. We came in a bit late for breakfast at actual lunch.

The lauk pauks have variety. I like them, suited to my taste although I prefer crunchy paru. The kangkong for the nasi lemak is chef’s kiss. The ikan bilis is top tier.

However the nasi was at the time was less fragrant. The sambal was less spicy and too sweet to my taste, but that is just my preference.

The drinks look good and had their Kopi ais less sweet so I guess it was okay.
Staff friendly. Food is good here especially nasi lemak. That sambal little bit spicy but its okay for me. Overall good. Happy day😁

formatted_address: 154, Jalan Petaling, City Centre, 50000 Kuala Lumpur, Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia
name: PALMIERRA 28 CAFE

reviews.text: Came across this place in China town. Good deal for lunch. Tried the buttermilk chicken which was good. The deal included unlimited rose water. The waiter was helpful and gave suggestions. Nice music in the background. All in all a good place and will surely return here.

Have to admit that the restaurant looks very pretty and has nice decor for people looking for socmed content. The food tasted decent but the pricing can be abit on the high side. Ordered the kari ikan lunch set for RM19.90 but was disappointed with the size of the fish. That being said, i still liked the taste of the fish curry but i just wished they gave a bigger portion for the lunch set. My colleagues ordered soto and they commented the taste was mediocre and had to order additional gravy/kuah for the dish.

Where to go for home-cooked authentic malay food in Petaling Street. Love every dish. I had fried rice with chicken tempoyak (fermented durian), the masak lemak tempoyak is well seasoned with thick gravy, so satisfying. Malay style mee curry noodles was thick, well seasoned, packed with condiments, ramen curry noodles is also delicious with so many condiments.

My favourite drink is lychee tea! So refreshing, the rest of drinks are made with love and worth for what they’re charging for. The orange juice is made with real orange and thick.

For dessert we had salted caramel cake, I like the butter taste because they used good butter. The cake is soft and love the salted caramel.

Come for lunch as their set comes with sirap orang kahwin at only MYR 16

The place is super instagrammable with mural on the walls and all the deco perfect for special day.
Ordered Nasi Dagang, Soto and Lontong from the breakfast menu. Lontong was my favourite! Looking forward to come again to try the lempeng!
If you want an authentic malay food/dishes, this is the place. Semua sedap!

formatted_address: 3, Jalan Ampang Putra, Taman Putra Sulaiman, 68000 Ampang, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Royale ‘Kedah’

reviews.text:
Tonight, I'm so dissatisfied and disappointed with the service. We've bought rice, chicken and gravy to eat at home. The portion of the rice were so little , it was unbelievable. One was even only enough for a few mouthfuls. I've realized that the portions had been smaller and smaller in the last of years, but it was still acceptable as the taste was somewhat still the same. I've been a regular since they first opened at the condo clubhouse. Back then, one nasi bungkus with chicken and veggies could be eaten by two people. Now, I finished my rice first before I can finish my small chicken wing. Mind you, not the whole part, just the wing itself. I hope things will change. The name Nasi Lemak Royale Kedah has nothing to do with Kedah at all. No Kedahan has been sighted and seen. Now, the food and service are also disheartening.

An update. I made an official complaint to the owner via the phone number given. The management apologized and had looked into the matter with the servers.

Fast service. Got two dining area, one with aircond (beside coffee shop) and one without aircond. Friendly staff. Generous portion. Affordable price. Dining area seems clean. But havent visit their toilet so couldnt give further comment abt clealiness.

top notch la dey😀 still a better food joint compared to their other branch in shah alam. Price wise, it’s reasonable.

Delicious mix of curry. Favorite is still telor sotong. Fried chicken is good too.

Normally packed to the brim especially during lunch time plus you need to line up.

Sometimes u craving for nasi kandar. I will visit once i want. Been a long time i come here. Just wanna tried after first review . Before, The kuah very sweet. But now, i will request a lil bit of kuah. So, taste good than before. And telur and ayam. Total RM17. Yeah, out of budget 🤪

Very tasty and affordable classic nasi lemak Kedah. Lunch is crowded so head there for dinner instead. Not your typical nasi lemak fr the mamak. I normally stick to the basic fried chicken, cabbage and salted egg but they have other options such as mutton, tiger prawn etc. Highly recommend this place for first timers as it will be a pretty exciting experience on your palate.

name: Tamparuli Nasi Lemak

reviews.text:
Heard abt this Nasi Lemak via social media and decide to take a drive and chk it out.

Overall good Nasi Lemak. Took the Sambal Petai Ikan Bilis, Beef Rendang, Fried Chicken And Sotong Sambal. 💪👍😎

The Sambal Was Not Bad As Well. Good Blend Of Spicy N Sweet, But More Towards The Spicy Side.

Bought 4 Packs Of Rice With The Other Condiments amounting to abt 32RM.

Will Definitely Come Back.

Side note, everyone has their own taste for food. If you feel it doesn't warrant a come back, don't throw a brick at them but do give constructive criticism to allow them to improve themselves 😊😉

Next to it, is a stall selling variety of Kueh2.. 👍👍👍
I ordered their nasi lemak paru + telur. It was proper, although the sambal was a bit too sweet for me.

On the table today is nasi lemak sambal paru and nasi lemak ayam berempah. So how does it taste?

Let me first tell you, they are very generous with the sambal. It's thick, smoky spicy sweet. The ikan bilis and kacang is old school, crunchy and you know it wasn't fried earlier as well. My soft spot is always paru but you only get slices usually. Ustaz gives you chunks. Yes, chunks. So right about now, the narrative is clear. This is one hell of a value nasi lemak for RM6. The flavours are very strong and if you like light tasting nasi lemak, then you will be overwhelmed

Nasi Lemak Jambatan Tamparuli opens in the morning but for Ramadan they start their business at 3-7pm. Queues form fast and parking is wherever you can find.

Sorry to say this but this stall is overrated. Overly long Q, the taste of the nasi lemak and the lauk are just average, so as the sambal. With this price you really can name a few eatery that is much better.

A new Nasi Lemak vendor in Shah Alam, but very established previously at its former location.

Delicious nasi lemak with hearty portion and variety of dishes at affordable price.

Hygienic, fast and friendly service.

Sometimes you have to queue a long line, yet it's worth it.

It opens only until afternoon, because it shares the same premise with another famous vendor for banana fritter i.e. Azmi Goreng Pisang.

formatted_address: No 11, Jalan Bola Jaring 13/15, Seksyen 13, 40100 Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Ikhwan Cafe Shah Alam

reviews.text: Clean and comfortable set up. Had our breakfast here. Served good roti canai. Also had lontong and nasi lemak. Reasonable pricing. Ample parking. Recommended 👍

Excellent lunch buffet. Very happy with tandoori chicken and nasi arab. They just recently moved to a new location down the street from their former shop. Extremely clean! Note: Friday is a charity operation and customers simply pay what they want into the charity money container.
Cheap food prices.  Delicious.  Must try.

Fantastique.! Clean, tidy outlet.
Tasty varieties foods. Atmosphere so calm..
Some food are good with a reasonable price. The cafe can improve vastly.

formatted_address: Lot G-96A5, Kompleks Pkns Shah Alam, Seksyen 14, 40505 Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Pop Meals @ PKNS

📋Nasi Ayam Kicap Sambal Gesek (Soy sauce chicken with chilli paste)

❤️definitely need to repeat this one. Like the name,its super creamy n cheesy with some chicken strip.

❤️Its so tasty. Creamy and thick gravy.the chicken also perfectly coated and fried
💵RM13.20
The food was good , the staff are friendly & the vibes are fine ✌🏻

All meals are so delicious. My favorite one is the Spicy Mac and Cheese. Foods here are a bit pricey but they give a lot of ingredients to make the meals. I never get a chance to dine in. But their apps make it easier.
Double charged for drinks but fortunely was changed with equivalent food. At first was advised to get refund tomorrow but after further nego the staff allowed to change with other item.

formatted_address: Seksyen 19, 40300 Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak CIAST

reviews.text: One of the best nasi lemak there is on shah alam. Gotta be early when buying nasi lemak here, if you come later than 8.30, you'll be queuing but don't worry, the nasi lemak sellers is very fast at packing up and they usually open counters with 3 guys packing it up. If you're a sambal person, need to request extra bcs it is not enough as it is delicious. Not to forget the amount of rice given can feed 2 persons with small stomach.

Today old man is at Seksyen 19 Shah Alam opposite a vocational college and a residential area. It's packed, people are waiting to order 4 or more packs in front of me. Everyone illegally parks, families come out for brekkie, a fireman shows up in full suit and a fire truck. We are all in line for nasi lemak.

On the table today is nasi lemak sambal paru with telor mata (RM6.50). Let's break this down. The sambal is sweet type with very little hint of spiciness. I thought that I wouldn't like this as I like the savoury sambal but this surprised me. A lot. The rice is very nice, reminds me of peak SS2 balai nasi lemak. Loose and individual. The anchovies (ikan bilis) is proper, crispy and salty. This will balance up the sweet sambal.

The star of the dish is the paru (cow lung). I've had rubbery and almost impossible to chew paru before but this is really nice and nothing like what I had before. Nice amount of chew, sweetness and saltiness. I had to do a double take to see if I was eating beef. The mix of sambal, ikan.bilis and paru from nasi lemak d'ciast goes really well. So it's not a surprise when people are willing to patiently wait 10 minutes for it to be cooked.

The queue starts at 7.30am and again parking is non-existent ( street parking). Dine in is available with the picnic tables at both sides. The wait can be long, sometimes 20 minutes above depending on how many packs is ordered in front of you. The base price is RM5.50. As I drove away, I turn to the opposite of the freeway and I see my next rendezvous. Stay tuned for the nasi lemak jambatan tamparuli.

*NOTE* This is not a paid post; the written content is based on author's personal opinion and preference.

For more food reviews, please follow me on Instagram at @seniorglutton thank you.
A well known 'unique nasi lemak' located just opposite the main gate of CIAST, Sect 19, Shah Alam is a must-visit place for risers' breakfast. Customers arrived earlier than the seller..😁

Best nasi lemak in Shah Alam by a long shot.
I will go to this spot at least twice per week.
The fragrance from the nasi lemak and sambal will make anyone drool. Their sambal paru and telur mata combo simply makes you feel satisfied like you accomplished something great in life.
Satisfaction point : 8/10

Food tastes good. There are three independent stalls: one stall selling drinks and two selling nasi lemak so you need to order separately. The two nasi lemak stalls are popular. Long queues are expected in the morning.

Parking is practically non existent. Patrons park their cars by the roadside.

Running water is not available. The stall operators bring in water in pails.
