reviews.text: I would recommend to try out this spot once. Sate for me was delicious. Savoury with a hint of sweetness & generous meat portion too. They have variety of food choices. I had tried their laksam, roti sarang burung, sate & lontong. All good but just skip for lontong cause taste of tumeric powder was too strong. Price wise was okay. Table can be limited during peak hours.

A very very wide range of Malay dishes and deserts.   The food is good.

Prices are reasonable.

But always full and busy during lunch, long queues. Very popular lunch stop. So don’t expect too much service.   Self-serve.

Parking may be a little difficult.
So much variety of Kelantan food , 4 of us ordered 4 different dishes like Nasi Kerabu and Laksam, but none of us finished our food . Taste lacking,  so so only.

Meat soup tastes salty. Ayam percik totally failed. Price for all food with warm water : Rm35

Not worth it for me.

I purposely went there to eat roti canai sarang.
Found the restaurant through KL Foodie TikTok channel.
So this review is ONLY about their roti canai.

They pre cooked the roti canai and served it upon request. So, please expect a not so warm kind of roti canai. I understand that they want to prevent the congestion of orders. I can still accept the cold roti canai in compensation of improving the speed of the service however the doh was tough and chewy. The dal and curry gravy were too sweet for me, it spoiled my appetite.

Quite expensive. We ate 2 roti sarang, 1 roti kosong, 1 hot teh o and 1 ice lime tea. The total was RM19.60.

formatted_address: 5, Jalan Ceongsam 10/11, Seksyen 10, 40100 Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Restoran Azira

reviews.text: Many selection, fast service. Food was delicious. Price still acceptable

Definitely one of the best breakfast & lunch spot in Shah Alam!
Been around since i was born and al most 3 decades later, they are still standing.
A lot of options.
Pay first before dining system, 2 cashiers, very fast queue. (Unless other customers cuts you 😡🤬)
Overall, the best place to grab breakfast and lunch.

Went for breakfast on 07/11/2024
I would say the price is a bit pricey for non air-conditioning restaurant
The taste were so-so
Rojak gravy was not spicy & the peanuts were too crushed.
Lempeng was too thick.while coconut lempeng was quite nice.

My first visit here around 10am on sunday..parking near shop a bit limited but you can park nearby houses.the breakfast dishes almost finish but vast varieties of kuih muih are still available. Tried the nasi lemak n the sambal for me was ok not that spicy a little sweet for my taste. Lots of other snack too..rojak mamak..mee kuah..pecal..lempeng..buah potong and goreng2 to name a few.since its almost 11am they started serving lunch..all the malay dishes were there..you name it!what a beautiful row of colors..n yes the table already full n people start coming n queing..so better come early while the food still hot n plenty

We came here again for lunch today, and without realizing it, I had almost the same thing for lunch!!!🤭🤣🤣🤣

This place is truly a blessing for all residents of Shah Alam...just look at the variety of food available on offer, and you will understand what I mean!! The breakfast spread alone is to die for, but the lunch spread never seems to end...and, they also cater for tea time and separate dinner menus...I just wonder, what time do they close? The local delicacies are mouth watering and delicious, and would certainly appeal to all walks of life, and the prices are very affordable too. This is definitely a place for me to dine on my cheat days!!

formatted_address: 12, Jalan RU 3/9a, Seksyen 3, 40000 Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Restoran Ceria

reviews.text:
I love to buy their Nasi Lemak with Ayam Goreng and Kuih Cakoi with Kaya.
Price: RM3 for Nasi Lemak Kosong, RM1 for each piece of Kuih Cakoi. Roti Canai is better to eat at the restaurant rather than bringing home. Their Roti Canai is crispy and their sambal is superb. I've been enjoying their food since I was a child and now I'm a grown up. Definitely worth the meal. Parking can be a hassle during weekends but weekdays is pretty okay. Their seating is using plastic chairs and plastic tables. There's outdoor and under the roof areas. Recommended to use cash only. There's no QR pay or card payment option seen at the cashier. You can read the menu and pricing at the cashier. All food are self service, no table service.

So we went for breakfast hunting here in Shah Alam.
The sambal nasi lemak is too sweet! No anchovies, so i would just give 1/5

Roti sarang burung is OK but mine is a bit burnt, anyway still acceptable so 3/5

Parking area is horrible. 20 mins to get the parking.

Overall 2/5. Will I come again? NO.

Went there for breakfast. Looks a bit run down from outside but quite clean. See my photos & videos to get a better feel. Quite a lot of people eating here. Tried the nasi lemak ayam goreng. It’s not the best i had, but ok. The chicken was freshly fried, nice & crispy. Tried the kuih chakoy. It was freshly fried. It was soo goodd. Crunchy outside, soft inside & warm. Plus dipped in the sauce, yumms! Must try it when its freshly fried. The staff here is also friendly & helpful. Good vibes.

Since we came very early morning as early as at 6.15 am....food is already in de shelf for us to choose. Nasi lemak, fried mee/meehoon/kueyteow n few traditional kueh , cakoi or even roti canai...etc. It is definitely good choice to have early breakfast. We even packed the food...to take away.😂

Those who like Nasi Lemak with sugar should opt this place. Nice flavour but too sweet...as sweet as nasi lemak CIAST. sweeter than typical kelantanese nasi lomak.
Their Bakso was good tho...

formatted_address: 63, Jln Batu Unjur, Taman Chi Liung, 42000 Pelabuhan Klang, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Basmathi - Taman Chi Liung

reviews.text: I came to this place because of a recommendation by a friend. Definitely one of the best Nasi Lemak I had even better it's using basmathi rice. The price, quality and the portion offered by them blows your mind. Definitely worth your money. The service was good but the shop a bit limited space for dine in.

Kumar Family video brings me here 😆.
Overall great nasi lemak but the rice is slightly oily. Fried chicken is good. Sambal & ikan bilis are not bad.
The rice portion is a lot.

Nasi lemak basmati rice have slight fragrance and portion is big. Sambal is normal not much surprise but I love their chicken which can choose party and quite big. Somehow the quality have to take note as sometimes ayam rempah is fragrance sometimes slightly tasteless. Price is cheap though and quite worth given the portion. Evening have lesser seating but after shop nearby close then there’s plenty enough seat. Waiting time is pretty long and need improvement.

This store has relocated from its original site to a new shop lot a few doors away.

Despite not having air-conditioning, it is cleaner, neater, better organised, and has a dining area.

I frequently purchase take-away(nasi lemak basmathi) that includes fried chicken, egg and sambal. The portion is generous considering the cost.

Pricing is reasonable as a packet can be shared between two people.

I ve’been eating here long time, great sambal belacan pair with nasi kukus. Ayam goreng is always cold but the crispiness did not compromise. Recommended to try out the Prwan noodles, very different from Chinese style and yet have the spicy kick with abundance of shrimp flavor.

name: Nasi Lemak Basmathi - Kampung Jawa

reviews.text: Order & pay direct at the counter, big portion for the Nasi Lemak set, suitable for 2 small people shared per plate & convenience for dine in to dinner time.. noon time kinda hot a bit as the restaurant concept is to open spaces facing the main road.

For a normal restaurant, this Nasi Lemak place is clean, efficient, service is fast.

Service:
1. Go to the order counter
2. Choose your food of choice (dine in/take out)
3. Menu is simole
4. Pay and wait for your order
5. They will call your number and even the grab number they will call
6. Food is hot and portion is big

The rice is fragrant and the chicken is huge. Anchovies are crispy.
Sambal not too spicy and not too sweet.

Price is really affordable for the portion.
Mi udang was nice too. Everything is just nice for the price and ambience

Visit here every time when I was super craving for a delicious nasi kukus ayam goreng🤤Their ayam goreng is top notch which really big and well seasoned fried!! 😋 The portion of their rice is super big too. If you're a small diet person you are recommended to share with your partner or friend🤣 In short, highly recommend 🔥

Opens 24 hours. Clean and well managed eatery. Probably as good as nasi lemak burung hantu but cheaper. Again it might not be cheaper as burung hantu comes with quarter chicken but here only 1/8 of the chicken albeit big size. The well cooked dark colored sambal has it all. Spicy, sweet with a hint of belacan. The basmati rice is fluffy but the choice of santan could’ve been better. It is very hard to get flavour consistency if using fresh santan. Other menu like sizzling yee mee, bakso and nasi kukus looks good as well but I didn’t try it. Drinks like teh ais was outstanding. My only gripe is it took so long to order as only 1 cashier to take order. I suggest increase the cashier or QR code ordering at the table.
First time here (04 Nov 2024) at 20:30. Not many people. Only one order counter make it quite slow to be your turn to make the order. The food portion quite big. Sambal not so spicy.

formatted_address: 12, Lorong Seraya, Taman Palm Grove, 41200 Klang, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Uncle Raju Kopitiam

reviews.text:
Parking could be very challenging around this kopitiam.  Super packed when we reached the kopitiam but everything still in order as they are using number service.
The Signature fried chicken is tender and juicy, must try if come here. Fried rice also very good.

Uncle Raju's Corner same row v uncle raju kopitiam, kopitiam open in the morning hour, while Uncle Raju Corner opened from 4pm to 1am. I went to  Uncle Raju's Corner on Friday evening, after 8pm getting crowded and crowded. they served local mamak foods. their foods are delicious, surprisingly tasty, and u will definitely go back again. they have some stalls selling Western food, keropok lekor, Korean bingsu, apam etc. recommended keropok lekor, even though u need to wait for it, but it is worth the waiting time. if u go on weekends, den ur waiting time for keropok lekor will be longer.lol. for mamak, u need to get a QR code to make an order. They served food fast n efficiency. chicken chop from Western food stall also not bad, if u don't like mamak foods, u can go for it. although not an air-conditioned dining environment, it's windy and comfortable to have ur meal here. overall is good, services are good, staff are friendly n helpful in Uncle Raju's Corner.
Cheap food and super yummy! The service here is extremely fast! Once you sit down, they will give you the utensils. It's definitely worth coming here. 👍

My Klang friend would laugh at me when they heard I have not been to Uncle Raju's Corner mamak since I am a Klangite. Probably the cleanest and most systematically managed mamak. Their stir fry stuffs (noodles, mihun, rice) has good wok hei (wok breath).

Roti stuffs are good too. Crispy on the surface. Drinks are hygienically packaged, and quite big on the serving size.

Came here for supper. Tried their mee goreng with ayam goreng and also roti tsunami. Food was surprisingly tasty just that the mee goreng is a bit wet and unspicy for my liking.

You can choose your curry topping for the roti tsunami. Added the dhal curry and fish curry. Fish curry was a bit sour probably due to tamarind. Roti was overall crispy and delicious. Teh ice was not sweet at all as  per request.

This mamak is located right in the middle of residential neighborhood so it is hard to find parking.

Aside from that, everything else was good and orderly. Getting a table fast - they will just pass your QR code for ordering and table no the moment you step in.

They also have other stalls such as apam, laksa, satay goreng, claypot briyani available.

formatted_address: TBG 1004, 70, Jln Tepi Sungai, Taman Wangi, 41100 Klang, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Restoran Kukus

reviews.text:
Place is preserve with 70-80 era decoration and setting with oldie musics. There’s parking behind which is an empty land. Indoor and outdoor seating available. Order through scan the QR code on table. Price is pretty affordable.

I Nasi kukus Ayam berempah is average but the sambal belacan is nice. It also came with free drinks so no need order extra. Lempeng serve hot and texture is great, the sambal that came with is quite spicy. Tongmo is really good as it was juicy and flavourful.

The only downside is might little bit hot on afternoon and the smoke of grill the tongmo will be all around the place and your whole body will be smoked with the smell.
Ayam Berempah was not tasty. However ubi kayu rebus & sambal ikan bilis is good. I believed Old Is Gold, retro ambiance setting in which makes the atmosphere only we as Malaysian would appreciate.
Old school P.Ramlee vibe with childhood 'Jajan' available for purchase brings back nostalgia. Order using app. Price is okay and taste could be better. Typical Nasi Kukus flavour.

Food was reasonably priced and tasty but it was quite stuffy in the afternoon. Service was not on par as I requested for a spoon for the asam pedas and the waiter just showed me where the spoon was instead of bringing me the spoon.

Authentic kampung-style cuisine. The food taste is superb, especially their curries, a must try. Very unusual dishes are available, nothing too commercial. Reasonable price and friendly staff. The atmosphere, with P. Ramlee songs in the background and classic interior designs, brings back a lot of memories from childhood. The only difficulty was finding a place to sit and the parking. You just have to be patience. Highly recommend this place.

formatted_address: 22, Jln Tiara 2C, Bandar Baru Klang, 41150 Klang, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Pak Li Kopitiam BBK, Klang

reviews.text: Food was great, especially their signature dishes such as their nasi lemak with rendang chic and lemon chicken rice. Do try their Ceylon tea as it’s fragrant and not too sweet. Cendol was delicious too. Place was clean and organized, service was fast and staffs are friendly. It’s quickly becoming a cozy and nice place to meet up with friends.
New & cozy. Weekend is the best time 😁 coz no need to worries about parking. Keep up the good quality & maintenance 💪
Favourite place to go. Good food, environment best. Really recommended this place. Sesuai untuk kids juga.
Good food, beautiful outdoor area to relax in and friendly staff and owner. 👍🏻
Iced White coffee taste booommm with affordable price. Only 4.50 👍🏻👍🏻  Good environments

formatted_address: 6, Jalan 21/11b, Sea Park, 46300 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
name: Nasi Lemak Bumbung

reviews.text: The place is so easy to find and it’s located in between the shop lots. The shop opens until 12 am but they open till 12:30 am since some customers come late. Just one request for the customers, please go there before 12 am since the workers also need to do their closing and back home. One of the craving nasi lemak in KL and it’s really taste good. They also have Burnt Cheesecake and Mango Stick Rice as an extra menus. Must try nasi Lemak and thank me later.

The place was very crowded at night, and I had to wait in line for a few minutes. I tried the nasi lemak ayam goreng for RM 8, and it was quite tasty. It's a great spot for nighttime dining with an open space.

Nasi lemak with fried egg and fried chicken cost RM8. Nasi has 'lemak' taste.. Chicken was slightly hard and sambal was not one of the best. However, the fried meehoon was good. Was not dry n had tomatoes which gave it both a savoury, spicy from the chili and sweet / sour from the tomatoes. Rendang chicken was alright too.

Dnt know how long ago was my last visit. Came here on a Monday night and didn't need to wait for a table which was nice.

This time round- I didn't wanna have their nasi lemak, I went for the Maggie goreng and it was satisfying. Good flavor. Somehow they cut the noodle into shorter length:') other than that, not bad at all!

The fried chicken is nice especially the outer layer, somehow the meat didn't felt like the spice went in. It was moist though.

I've been a frequent visitor for the past 20 years. I've always liked their food . Started off with indo Mee and today they've got varieties and even started with a POS system to collect payment from customers. I used to admire all their staff's super quick maths during the "boss Kira" time. Their service is really fast and accurate most of the time. In terms of cleanliness you can't expect much because your seating areas are between road alleys. Honestly the drain and cockroaches freaks me out. Other than that this place brings me back to my teenage days. I will only order their indo Mee and Milo Ais and that's the best.
